    #[test]
    fn test_detect_language() {
        let extractor = CoverageExtractor::default();
        
        assert_eq!(extractor.detect_language(&amp;PathBuf::from(&quot;test.py&quot;)), &quot;python&quot;);
        assert_eq!(extractor.detect_language(&amp;PathBuf::from(&quot;test.js&quot;)), &quot;javascript&quot;);
        assert_eq!(extractor.detect_language(&amp;PathBuf::from(&quot;test.ts&quot;)), &quot;typescript&quot;);
        assert_eq!(extractor.detect_language(&amp;PathBuf::from(&quot;test.rs&quot;)), &quot;rust&quot;);
        assert_eq!(extractor.detect_language(&amp;PathBuf::from(&quot;test.go&quot;)), &quot;go&quot;);
        assert_eq!(extractor.detect_language(&amp;PathBuf::from(&quot;test.java&quot;)), &quot;java&quot;);
        assert_eq!(extractor.detect_language(&amp;PathBuf::from(&quot;test.cpp&quot;)), &quot;cpp&quot;);
        assert_eq!(extractor.detect_language(&amp;PathBuf::from(&quot;test.c&quot;)), &quot;c&quot;);
        assert_eq!(extractor.detect_language(&amp;PathBuf::from(&quot;test.txt&quot;)), &quot;unknown&quot;);
    }

    #[test]
    fn test_coalesce_spans_for_file() {
        let extractor = CoverageExtractor::default();
        
        // Test empty input
        assert!(extractor.coalesce_spans_for_file(&amp;[]).unwrap().is_empty());
        
        // Test single span
        let spans = vec![
            UncoveredSpan {
                path: PathBuf::from(&quot;test.py&quot;),
                start: 5,
                end: 5,
                hits: Some(0),
            }
        ];
        let result = extractor.coalesce_spans_for_file(&amp;spans).unwrap();
        assert_eq!(result.len(), 1);
        assert_eq!(result[0].start, 5);
        assert_eq!(result[0].end, 5);
        
        // Test adjacent spans (should merge)
        let spans = vec![
            UncoveredSpan {
                path: PathBuf::from(&quot;test.py&quot;),
                start: 5,
                end: 5,
                hits: Some(0),
            },
            UncoveredSpan {
                path: PathBuf::from(&quot;test.py&quot;),
                start: 6,
                end: 6,
                hits: Some(0),
            },
            UncoveredSpan {
                path: PathBuf::from(&quot;test.py&quot;),
                start: 7,
                end: 8,
                hits: Some(0),
            }
        ];
        let result = extractor.coalesce_spans_for_file(&amp;spans).unwrap();
        assert_eq!(result.len(), 1);
        assert_eq!(result[0].start, 5);
        assert_eq!(result[0].end, 8);
        
        // Test spans with gaps (should not merge if gap &gt; 3 lines)
        let spans = vec![
            UncoveredSpan {
                path: PathBuf::from(&quot;test.py&quot;),
                start: 1,
                end: 2,
                hits: Some(0),
            },
            UncoveredSpan {
                path: PathBuf::from(&quot;test.py&quot;),
                start: 10,
                end: 12,
                hits: Some(0),
            }
        ];
        let result = extractor.coalesce_spans_for_file(&amp;spans).unwrap();
        assert_eq!(result.len(), 2);
        assert_eq!(result[0].start, 1);
        assert_eq!(result[0].end, 2);
        assert_eq!(result[1].start, 10);
        assert_eq!(result[1].end, 12);
        
        // Test spans with small gaps (should merge if gap &lt;= 3 lines)
        let spans = vec![
            UncoveredSpan {
                path: PathBuf::from(&quot;test.py&quot;),
                start: 1,
                end: 2,
                hits: Some(0),
            },
            UncoveredSpan {
                path: PathBuf::from(&quot;test.py&quot;),
                start: 5,
                end: 6,
                hits: Some(0),
            }
        ];
        let result = extractor.coalesce_spans_for_file(&amp;spans).unwrap();
        assert_eq!(result.len(), 1);
        assert_eq!(result[0].start, 1);
        assert_eq!(result[0].end, 6);
    }

    #[test]
    fn test_coalesce_gaps_basic() {
        let extractor = CoverageExtractor::default();
        
        // Test with simple uncovered spans
        let spans = vec![
            UncoveredSpan {
                path: PathBuf::from(&quot;test.py&quot;),
                start: 5,
                end: 7,
                hits: Some(0),
            },
            UncoveredSpan {
                path: PathBuf::from(&quot;test.js&quot;),
                start: 10,
                end: 12,
                hits: Some(0),
            }
        ];
        
        let gaps = extractor.coalesce_gaps(spans).unwrap();
        assert_eq!(gaps.len(), 2);
        
        // Check Python gap
        let py_gap = gaps.iter().find(|g| g.language == &quot;python&quot;).unwrap();
        assert_eq!(py_gap.span.start, 5);
        assert_eq!(py_gap.span.end, 7);
        assert_eq!(py_gap.features.gap_loc, 3);
        
        // Check JavaScript gap  
        let js_gap = gaps.iter().find(|g| g.language == &quot;javascript&quot;).unwrap();
        assert_eq!(js_gap.span.start, 10);
        assert_eq!(js_gap.span.end, 12);
        assert_eq!(js_gap.features.gap_loc, 3);
    }

    #[test]
    fn test_chunk_spans_python_small_span() {
        let extractor = CoverageExtractor::default();
        
        // Create a temporary Python file for testing
        let temp_dir = std::env::temp_dir();
        let test_file = temp_dir.join(&quot;chunk_test_small.py&quot;);
        fs::write(&amp;test_file, r#&quot;def function1():
    print(&quot;hello&quot;)
    return True

def function2():
    return False
&quot;#).unwrap();
        
        // Small span (&lt;=5 lines) should not be chunked
        let spans = vec![
            UncoveredSpan {
                path: test_file.clone(),
                start: 1,
                end: 3,
                hits: Some(0),
            }
        ];
        
        let result = extractor.chunk_spans_python(&amp;test_file, &amp;spans).unwrap();
        assert_eq!(result.len(), 1);
        assert_eq!(result[0].start, 1);
        assert_eq!(result[0].end, 3);
        
        fs::remove_file(test_file).ok();
    }

    #[test]
    fn test_chunk_spans_python_large_span() {
        let extractor = CoverageExtractor::default();
        
        // Create a temporary Python file with multiple functions
        let temp_dir = std::env::temp_dir();
        let test_file = temp_dir.join(&quot;chunk_test_large.py&quot;);
        fs::write(&amp;test_file, r#&quot;# Line 1
def function1():
    print(&quot;function 1&quot;)
    return True

def function2():
    print(&quot;function 2&quot;)  
    return False

class MyClass:
    def method1(self):
        return &quot;method1&quot;
        
    async def method2(self):
        return &quot;method2&quot;
&quot;#).unwrap();
        
        // Large span (&gt;5 lines) should be chunked at function/class boundaries
        let spans = vec![
            UncoveredSpan {
                path: test_file.clone(),
                start: 1,
                end: 15,
                hits: Some(0),
            }
        ];
        
        let result = extractor.chunk_spans_python(&amp;test_file, &amp;spans).unwrap();
        
        // Should be chunked into multiple spans at function/class boundaries
        assert!(result.len() &gt; 1);
        
        // Verify that chunks respect the original span boundaries
        for chunk in &amp;result {
            assert!(chunk.start &gt;= 1);
            assert!(chunk.end &lt;= 15);
            assert!(chunk.start &lt;= chunk.end);
        }
        
        fs::remove_file(test_file).ok();
    }

    #[test]
    fn test_chunk_spans_by_language_unknown() {
        let extractor = CoverageExtractor::default();
        
        let spans = vec![
            UncoveredSpan {
                path: PathBuf::from(&quot;test.unknown&quot;),
                start: 1,
                end: 10,
                hits: Some(0),
            }
        ];
        
        let result = extractor.chunk_spans_by_language(&amp;PathBuf::from(&quot;test.unknown&quot;), &quot;unknown&quot;, &amp;spans).unwrap();
        assert_eq!(result.len(), 1);
        assert_eq!(result[0].start, 1);
        assert_eq!(result[0].end, 10);
    }

    #[test]
    fn test_normalize_size_score() {
        let extractor = CoverageExtractor::default();
        
        assert_eq!(extractor.normalize_size_score(0), 0.0);
        assert!(extractor.normalize_size_score(10) &gt; 0.3);
        assert!(extractor.normalize_size_score(20) &gt; 0.4);
        assert!(extractor.normalize_size_score(100) &lt; 1.0); // Should have diminishing returns
    }

    #[test]
    fn test_normalize_complexity_score() {
        let extractor = CoverageExtractor::default();
        
        assert_eq!(extractor.normalize_complexity_score(0.0), 0.0);
        assert!(extractor.normalize_complexity_score(5.0) &gt; 0.3);
        assert!(extractor.normalize_complexity_score(10.0) &gt; 0.4);
        assert!(extractor.normalize_complexity_score(100.0) &lt; 1.0); // Should have diminishing returns
    }

    #[test]
    fn test_normalize_fan_in_score() {
        let extractor = CoverageExtractor::default();
        
        assert_eq!(extractor.normalize_fan_in_score(0), 0.0);
        assert!(extractor.normalize_fan_in_score(2) &gt; 0.2);
        assert!(extractor.normalize_fan_in_score(5) &gt; 0.4);
        assert!(extractor.normalize_fan_in_score(50) &lt; 1.0); // Should have diminishing returns
    }

    #[test]
    fn test_estimate_file_centrality() {
        let extractor = CoverageExtractor::default();
        
        // High centrality files
        assert_eq!(extractor.estimate_file_centrality(&amp;PathBuf::from(&quot;src/lib.rs&quot;)), 0.9);
        assert_eq!(extractor.estimate_file_centrality(&amp;PathBuf::from(&quot;src/main.rs&quot;)), 0.9);
        assert_eq!(extractor.estimate_file_centrality(&amp;PathBuf::from(&quot;__init__.py&quot;)), 0.9);
        
        // Medium centrality
        assert_eq!(extractor.estimate_file_centrality(&amp;PathBuf::from(&quot;src/core/mod.rs&quot;)), 0.7);
        assert_eq!(extractor.estimate_file_centrality(&amp;PathBuf::from(&quot;src/common/utils.rs&quot;)), 0.7);
        
        // Low centrality
        assert_eq!(extractor.estimate_file_centrality(&amp;PathBuf::from(&quot;tests/test_example.py&quot;)), 0.2);
        
        // Default centrality
        assert_eq!(extractor.estimate_file_centrality(&amp;PathBuf::from(&quot;src/feature/handler.rs&quot;)), 0.5);
    }

    #[test]
    fn test_extract_symbol_from_line() {
        let extractor = CoverageExtractor::default();
        
        // Function detection
        let symbol = extractor.extract_symbol_from_line(&quot;fn calculate_score(x: i32) -&gt; f64 {&quot;, 42);
        assert!(symbol.is_some());
        let symbol = symbol.unwrap();
        assert_eq!(symbol.kind, SymbolKind::Function);
        assert_eq!(symbol.name, &quot;calculate_score&quot;);
        assert_eq!(symbol.line_start, 42);
        
        // Python function
        let symbol = extractor.extract_symbol_from_line(&quot;def process_data(items):&quot;, 10);
        assert!(symbol.is_some());
        let symbol = symbol.unwrap();
        assert_eq!(symbol.kind, SymbolKind::Function);
        assert_eq!(symbol.name, &quot;process_data&quot;);
        
        // Class detection
        let symbol = extractor.extract_symbol_from_line(&quot;class DataProcessor {&quot;, 5);
        assert!(symbol.is_some());
        let symbol = symbol.unwrap();
        assert_eq!(symbol.kind, SymbolKind::Class);
        assert_eq!(symbol.name, &quot;DataProcessor&quot;);
        
        // No symbol
        let symbol = extractor.extract_symbol_from_line(&quot;let x = 42;&quot;, 1);
        assert!(symbol.is_none());
    }

    #[test]
    fn test_score_gaps_basic() {
        let extractor = CoverageExtractor::default();
        
        // Create test gaps with different characteristics
        let mut gaps = vec![
            CoverageGap {
                path: PathBuf::from(&quot;src/lib.rs&quot;), // High centrality
                span: UncoveredSpan {
                    path: PathBuf::from(&quot;src/lib.rs&quot;),
                    start: 1,
                    end: 10, // Medium size
                    hits: Some(0),
                },
                file_loc: 100,
                language: &quot;rust&quot;.to_string(),
                score: 0.0,
                features: GapFeatures {
                    gap_loc: 10,
                    cyclomatic_in_gap: 3.0, // Some complexity
                    cognitive_in_gap: 2.0,
                    fan_in_gap: 2,
                    exports_touched: true, // Public API
                    dependency_centrality_file: 0.0, // Will be updated
                    interface_surface: 0,
                    docstring_or_comment_present: false, // Missing docs
                    exception_density_in_gap: 0.0,
                },
                symbols: Vec::new(),
                preview: SnippetPreview {
                    language: &quot;rust&quot;.to_string(),
                    pre: Vec::new(),
                    head: Vec::new(),
                    tail: Vec::new(),
                    post: Vec::new(),
                    markers: GapMarkers { start_line: 1, end_line: 10 },
                    imports: Vec::new(),
                },
            },
            CoverageGap {
                path: PathBuf::from(&quot;tests/test.rs&quot;), // Low centrality
                span: UncoveredSpan {
                    path: PathBuf::from(&quot;tests/test.rs&quot;),
                    start: 20,
                    end: 22, // Small size
                    hits: Some(0),
                },
                file_loc: 50,
                language: &quot;rust&quot;.to_string(),
                score: 0.0,
                features: GapFeatures {
                    gap_loc: 3,
                    cyclomatic_in_gap: 0.0, // No complexity
                    cognitive_in_gap: 0.0,
                    fan_in_gap: 0,
                    exports_touched: false, // Private
                    dependency_centrality_file: 0.0, // Will be updated
                    interface_surface: 0,
                    docstring_or_comment_present: true, // Has docs
                    exception_density_in_gap: 0.0,
                },
                symbols: Vec::new(),
                preview: SnippetPreview {
                    language: &quot;rust&quot;.to_string(),
                    pre: Vec::new(),
                    head: Vec::new(),
                    tail: Vec::new(),
                    post: Vec::new(),
                    markers: GapMarkers { start_line: 20, end_line: 22 },
                    imports: Vec::new(),
                },
            },
        ];
        
        extractor.score_gaps(&amp;mut gaps).unwrap();
        
        // Should be sorted by score descending
        assert!(gaps[0].score &gt; gaps[1].score);
        
        // The lib.rs gap should score higher due to:
        // - Higher centrality (lib.rs vs test.rs) 
        // - Larger size (10 vs 3 lines)
        // - Higher complexity (5.0 vs 0.0 total)
        // - Public exports (true vs false)
        // - Missing docs (gets points for needing docs)
        assert_eq!(gaps[0].path, PathBuf::from(&quot;src/lib.rs&quot;));
        assert_eq!(gaps[1].path, PathBuf::from(&quot;tests/test.rs&quot;));
        
        // Scores should be in [0.0, 1.0] range
        for gap in &amp;gaps {
            assert!(gap.score &gt;= 0.0 &amp;&amp; gap.score &lt;= 1.0);
        }
    }

    #[test]
    fn test_extract_lines() {
        let extractor = CoverageExtractor::default();
        let lines = vec![&quot;line1&quot;, &quot;line2&quot;, &quot;line3&quot;, &quot;line4&quot;, &quot;line5&quot;];
        
        // Normal case
        let result = extractor.extract_lines(&amp;lines, 2, 4);
        assert_eq!(result.len(), 3);
        assert_eq!(result[0], &quot;   2 | line2&quot;);
        assert_eq!(result[1], &quot;   3 | line3&quot;);
        assert_eq!(result[2], &quot;   4 | line4&quot;);
        
        // Edge cases
        assert!(extractor.extract_lines(&amp;lines, 0, 2).is_empty()); // start = 0
        assert!(extractor.extract_lines(&amp;lines, 3, 2).is_empty()); // start &gt; end
        assert!(extractor.extract_lines(&amp;lines, 10, 12).is_empty()); // out of bounds
        
        // Single line
        let result = extractor.extract_lines(&amp;lines, 1, 1);
        assert_eq!(result.len(), 1);
        assert_eq!(result[0], &quot;   1 | line1&quot;);
    }

    #[test]
    fn test_extract_imports_python() {
        let extractor = CoverageExtractor::default();
        let lines = vec![
            &quot;#!/usr/bin/env python3&quot;,
            &quot;import os&quot;,
            &quot;import sys&quot;,
            &quot;from collections import defaultdict&quot;,
            &quot;from typing import List, Dict&quot;,
            &quot;&quot;,
            &quot;def some_function():&quot;,
            &quot;    pass&quot;,
        ];
        
        let imports = extractor.extract_imports(&amp;lines, &quot;python&quot;);
        assert!(imports.contains(&amp;&quot;import os&quot;.to_string()));
        assert!(imports.contains(&amp;&quot;import sys&quot;.to_string()));
        assert!(imports.contains(&amp;&quot;from collections import defaultdict&quot;.to_string()));
        assert!(imports.contains(&amp;&quot;from typing import List, Dict&quot;.to_string()));
        assert!(!imports.contains(&amp;&quot;def some_function():&quot;.to_string()));
    }

    #[test]
    fn test_extract_imports_rust() {
        let extractor = CoverageExtractor::default();
        let lines = vec![
            &quot;use std::collections::HashMap;&quot;,
            &quot;use std::fs;&quot;,
            &quot;use crate::core::errors::Result;&quot;,
            &quot;&quot;,
            &quot;fn main() {&quot;,
            &quot;    println!(\&quot;Hello\&quot;);&quot;,
            &quot;}&quot;,
        ];
        
        let imports = extractor.extract_imports(&amp;lines, &quot;rust&quot;);
        assert!(imports.contains(&amp;&quot;use std::collections::HashMap;&quot;.to_string()));
        assert!(imports.contains(&amp;&quot;use std::fs;&quot;.to_string()));
        assert!(imports.contains(&amp;&quot;use crate::core::errors::Result;&quot;.to_string()));
        assert!(!imports.contains(&amp;&quot;fn main() {&quot;.to_string()));
    }

    #[test]
    fn test_extract_imports_typescript() {
        let extractor = CoverageExtractor::default();
        let lines = vec![
            &quot;import React from &#x27;react&#x27;;&quot;,
            &quot;import { useState, useEffect } from &#x27;react&#x27;;&quot;, 
            &quot;import type { User } from &#x27;./types&#x27;;&quot;,
            &quot;const fs = require(&#x27;fs&#x27;);&quot;,
            &quot;&quot;,
            &quot;function Component() {&quot;,
            &quot;  return &lt;div&gt;Hello&lt;/div&gt;;&quot;,
            &quot;}&quot;,
        ];
        
        let imports = extractor.extract_imports(&amp;lines, &quot;typescript&quot;);
        assert!(imports.contains(&amp;&quot;import React from &#x27;react&#x27;;&quot;.to_string()));
        assert!(imports.contains(&amp;&quot;import { useState, useEffect } from &#x27;react&#x27;;&quot;.to_string()));
        assert!(imports.contains(&amp;&quot;import type { User } from &#x27;./types&#x27;;&quot;.to_string()));
        assert!(imports.contains(&amp;&quot;const fs = require(&#x27;fs&#x27;);&quot;.to_string()));
        assert!(!imports.contains(&amp;&quot;function Component() {&quot;.to_string()));
    }

    #[test]
    fn test_generate_preview_with_real_file() {
        let extractor = CoverageExtractor::default();
        
        // Create a temporary file for testing
        let temp_dir = std::env::temp_dir();
        let test_file = temp_dir.join(&quot;preview_test.py&quot;);
        fs::write(&amp;test_file, r#&quot;#!/usr/bin/env python3
import os
import sys
from collections import defaultdict

def function_one():
    &quot;&quot;&quot;This function is covered by tests.&quot;&quot;&quot;
    return &quot;covered&quot;

def untested_function():
    # This function has no tests - should appear in gap
    if True:
        return &quot;untested&quot;
    else:
        return &quot;never reached&quot;
        
def another_untested():
    &quot;&quot;&quot;Another untested function&quot;&quot;&quot;  
    x = 1 + 1
    return x

def final_function():
    return &quot;also covered&quot;
&quot;#).unwrap();
        
        // Create a gap that covers the untested functions
        let gap = CoverageGap {
            path: test_file.clone(),
            span: UncoveredSpan {
                path: test_file.clone(),
                start: 10, // untested_function starts here
                end: 18,   // another_untested ends here
                hits: Some(0),
            },
            file_loc: 100,
            language: &quot;python&quot;.to_string(),
            score: 0.0,
            features: GapFeatures {
                gap_loc: 9,
                cyclomatic_in_gap: 0.0,
                cognitive_in_gap: 0.0,
                fan_in_gap: 0,
                exports_touched: false,
                dependency_centrality_file: 0.0,
                interface_surface: 0,
                docstring_or_comment_present: false,
                exception_density_in_gap: 0.0,
            },
            symbols: Vec::new(),
            preview: SnippetPreview {
                language: &quot;python&quot;.to_string(),
                pre: Vec::new(),
                head: Vec::new(),
                tail: Vec::new(),
                post: Vec::new(),
                markers: GapMarkers { start_line: 10, end_line: 18 },
                imports: Vec::new(),
            },
        };
        
        let preview = extractor.generate_preview(&amp;gap).unwrap();
        
        // Verify the preview structure
        assert_eq!(preview.language, &quot;python&quot;);
        assert_eq!(preview.markers.start_line, 10);
        assert_eq!(preview.markers.end_line, 18);
        
        // Should have context before the gap
        assert!(!preview.pre.is_empty());
        assert!(preview.pre.iter().any(|line| line.contains(&quot;return \&quot;covered\&quot;&quot;)));
        
        // Should have gap content (all in head since it&#x27;s a short gap)
        assert!(!preview.head.is_empty());
        assert!(preview.head.iter().any(|line| line.contains(&quot;untested_function&quot;)));
        
        // Should have context after the gap  
        assert!(!preview.post.is_empty());
        assert!(preview.post.iter().any(|line| line.contains(&quot;final_function&quot;)));
        
        // Should have extracted Python imports
        assert!(!preview.imports.is_empty());
        assert!(preview.imports.contains(&amp;&quot;import os&quot;.to_string()));
        assert!(preview.imports.contains(&amp;&quot;import sys&quot;.to_string()));
        assert!(preview.imports.contains(&amp;&quot;from collections import defaultdict&quot;.to_string()));
        
        fs::remove_file(test_file).ok();
    }

    #[test]
    fn test_generate_preview_long_gap() {
        let extractor = CoverageExtractor::default();
        
        // Create a temporary file with a long gap
        let temp_dir = std::env::temp_dir();
        let test_file = temp_dir.join(&quot;long_gap_test.py&quot;);
        let long_content = (1..=50).map(|i| format!(&quot;    line_{} = {}&quot;, i, i)).collect::&lt;Vec&lt;_&gt;&gt;().join(&quot;\n&quot;);
        fs::write(&amp;test_file, format!(&quot;def big_function():\n{}\n    return total&quot;, long_content)).unwrap();
        
        // Create a gap that covers most of the function (line 2-51)
        let gap = CoverageGap {
            path: test_file.clone(),
            span: UncoveredSpan {
                path: test_file.clone(),
                start: 2,
                end: 51,
                hits: Some(0),
            },
            file_loc: 100,
            language: &quot;python&quot;.to_string(),
            score: 0.0,
            features: GapFeatures {
                gap_loc: 50,
                cyclomatic_in_gap: 0.0,
                cognitive_in_gap: 0.0,
                fan_in_gap: 0,
                exports_touched: false,
                dependency_centrality_file: 0.0,
                interface_surface: 0,
                docstring_or_comment_present: false,
                exception_density_in_gap: 0.0,
            },
            symbols: Vec::new(),
            preview: SnippetPreview {
                language: &quot;python&quot;.to_string(),
                pre: Vec::new(),
                head: Vec::new(),
                tail: Vec::new(),
                post: Vec::new(),
                markers: GapMarkers { start_line: 2, end_line: 51 },
                imports: Vec::new(),
            },
        };
        
        let preview = extractor.generate_preview(&amp;gap).unwrap();
        
        // For a long gap, should have both head and tail sections
        assert!(!preview.head.is_empty());
        assert!(!preview.tail.is_empty());
        
        // Head should contain early lines
        assert!(preview.head.iter().any(|line| line.contains(&quot;line_1 = 1&quot;)));
        
        // Tail should contain later lines
        assert!(preview.tail.iter().any(|line| line.contains(&quot;line_50 = 50&quot;)));
        
        // Should have context before (function definition)
        assert!(!preview.pre.is_empty());
        assert!(preview.pre.iter().any(|line| line.contains(&quot;def big_function&quot;)));
        
        // Should have context after (return statement)
        assert!(!preview.post.is_empty());
        assert!(preview.post.iter().any(|line| line.contains(&quot;return total&quot;)));
        
        fs::remove_file(test_file).ok();
    }

    #[tokio::test]
    async fn test_build_coverage_packs_integration() {
        let config = CoverageConfig {
            enabled: true,
            report_paths: vec![PathBuf::from(&quot;coverage.lcov&quot;)],
            max_gaps_per_file: 5,
            min_gap_loc: 1, // Lower threshold for testing
            snippet_context_lines: 3,
            long_gap_head_tail: 5,
            group_cross_file: false,
            target_repo_gain: 0.10,
            weights: ScoringWeights::default(),
            exclude_patterns: vec![&quot;*/tests/*&quot;.to_string()],
        };
        
        let mut extractor = CoverageExtractor::new(config);
        
        // Only run if the coverage file exists
        if std::path::Path::new(&quot;coverage.lcov&quot;).exists() {
            let coverage_reports = vec![PathBuf::from(&quot;coverage.lcov&quot;)];
            let result = extractor.build_coverage_packs(coverage_reports).await;
            
            match result {
                Ok(packs) =&gt; {
                    println!(&quot;✅ Generated {} coverage packs&quot;, packs.len());
                    
                    for (i, pack) in packs.iter().enumerate().take(2) {
                        println!(&quot;📦 Pack #{}: {} (file: {:?})&quot;, i+1, pack.pack_id, pack.path);
                        println!(&quot;   Gaps: {}, File LOC: {}, Coverage gain: {:.2}%&quot;, 
                            pack.gaps.len(), pack.file_info.loc, pack.value.file_cov_gain * 100.0);
                        
                        for (j, gap) in pack.gaps.iter().enumerate().take(1) {
                            println!(&quot;   🔸 Gap #{}: lines {}-{}, score: {:.3}, lang: {}&quot;, 
                                j+1, gap.span.start, gap.span.end, gap.score, gap.language);
                        }
                    }
                },
                Err(e) =&gt; {
                    println!(&quot;⚠️  Coverage pack generation failed (this is expected in test environment): {}&quot;, e);
                }
            }
        } else {
            println!(&quot;⚠️  No coverage.lcov file found - skipping integration test&quot;);
        }
    }
}

//! Configuration structs, data types, and core types for structure analysis

use petgraph::{Directed, Graph, Undirected};
use serde::{Deserialize, Serialize};
use std::collections::HashSet;
use std::path::PathBuf;

/// Configuration for structure analysis
#[derive(Debug, Clone, Serialize, Deserialize)]
pub struct StructureConfig {
    /// Enable branch reorganization packs
    pub enable_branch_packs: bool,
    /// Enable file split packs
    pub enable_file_split_packs: bool,
    /// Maximum number of top packs to return
    pub top_packs: usize,
    /// File system directory settings
    pub fsdir: FsDirectoryConfig,
    /// File system file settings
    pub fsfile: FsFileConfig,
    /// Graph partitioning settings
    pub partitioning: PartitioningConfig,
}

#[derive(Debug, Clone, Serialize, Deserialize)]
pub struct StructureToggles {
    /// Enable branch reorganization packs
    pub enable_branch_packs: bool,
    /// Enable file split packs
    pub enable_file_split_packs: bool,
    /// Maximum number of top packs to return
    pub top_packs: usize,
}

#[derive(Debug, Clone, Serialize, Deserialize)]
pub struct FsDirectoryConfig {
    /// Maximum files per directory before pressure
    pub max_files_per_dir: usize,
    /// Maximum subdirectories per directory before pressure
    pub max_subdirs_per_dir: usize,
    /// Maximum lines of code per directory before pressure
    pub max_dir_loc: usize,
    /// Minimum imbalance gain required for branch recommendation
    pub min_branch_recommendation_gain: f64,
    /// Minimum files required before considering directory split
    pub min_files_for_split: usize,
    /// Target lines of code per subdirectory when partitioning
    pub target_loc_per_subdir: usize,
}

#[derive(Debug, Clone, Serialize, Deserialize)]
pub struct FsFileConfig {
    /// Lines of code threshold for huge files
    pub huge_loc: usize,
    /// Byte size threshold for huge files
    pub huge_bytes: usize,
    /// Minimum lines of code before considering file split
    pub min_split_loc: usize,
    /// Minimum entities per file split
    pub min_entities_per_split: usize,
}

#[derive(Debug, Clone, Serialize, Deserialize)]
pub struct PartitioningConfig {
    /// Balance tolerance for partitioning (0.25 = ±25%)
    pub balance_tolerance: f64,
    /// Maximum number of clusters per partition
    pub max_clusters: usize,
    /// Minimum number of clusters per partition
    pub min_clusters: usize,
    /// Fallback names for clusters when automatic naming fails
    pub naming_fallbacks: Vec&lt;String&gt;,
}

impl Default for StructureConfig {
    fn default() -&gt; Self {
        Self {
            enable_branch_packs: true,
            enable_file_split_packs: true,
            top_packs: 20,
            fsdir: FsDirectoryConfig {
                max_files_per_dir: 25,
                max_subdirs_per_dir: 10,
                max_dir_loc: 2000,
                min_branch_recommendation_gain: 0.15,
                min_files_for_split: 5,
                target_loc_per_subdir: 1000,
            },
            fsfile: FsFileConfig {
                huge_loc: 800,
                huge_bytes: 128_000,
                min_split_loc: 200,
                min_entities_per_split: 3,
            },
            partitioning: PartitioningConfig {
                balance_tolerance: 0.25,
                max_clusters: 4,
                min_clusters: 2,
                naming_fallbacks: vec![
                    &quot;core&quot;.to_string(),
                    &quot;io&quot;.to_string(),
                    &quot;api&quot;.to_string(),
                    &quot;util&quot;.to_string(),
                ],
            },
        }
    }
}

/// Directory metrics for imbalance calculation
#[derive(Debug, Clone, Serialize)]
pub struct DirectoryMetrics {
    /// Number of files in directory
    pub files: usize,
    /// Number of subdirectories
    pub subdirs: usize,
    /// Total lines of code
    pub loc: usize,
    /// Gini coefficient of LOC distribution
    pub gini: f64,
    /// Entropy of LOC distribution
    pub entropy: f64,
    /// File pressure (files / max_files_per_dir)
    pub file_pressure: f64,
    /// Branch pressure (subdirs / max_subdirs_per_dir)
    pub branch_pressure: f64,
    /// Size pressure (loc / max_dir_loc)
    pub size_pressure: f64,
    /// Dispersion metric combining gini and entropy
    pub dispersion: f64,
    /// Overall imbalance score
    pub imbalance: f64,
}

/// Branch reorganization pack recommendation
#[derive(Debug, Clone, Serialize)]
pub struct BranchReorgPack {
    /// Type identifier
    pub kind: String,
    /// Directory path
    pub dir: PathBuf,
    /// Current directory state
    pub current: DirectoryMetrics,
    /// Proposed partitions
    pub proposal: Vec&lt;DirectoryPartition&gt;,
    /// File move operations
    pub file_moves: Vec&lt;FileMove&gt;,
    /// Expected gains from reorganization
    pub gain: ReorganizationGain,
    /// Estimated effort for reorganization
    pub effort: ReorganizationEffort,
    /// Rules and constraints
    pub rules: Vec&lt;String&gt;,
}

/// Proposed directory partition
#[derive(Debug, Clone, Serialize)]
pub struct DirectoryPartition {
    /// Suggested partition name
    pub name: String,
    /// Files to move to this partition
    pub files: Vec&lt;PathBuf&gt;,
    /// Total lines of code in partition
    pub loc: usize,
}

/// Expected gains from reorganization
#[derive(Debug, Clone, Serialize)]
pub struct ReorganizationGain {
    /// Change in imbalance score (positive = improvement)
    pub imbalance_delta: f64,
    /// Number of cross-cluster edges reduced
    pub cross_edges_reduced: usize,
}

/// Effort estimation for reorganization
#[derive(Debug, Clone, Serialize)]
pub struct ReorganizationEffort {
    /// Number of files that need to be moved
    pub files_moved: usize,
    /// Estimated number of import statement updates
    pub import_updates_est: usize,
}

/// File move operation
#[derive(Debug, Clone, Serialize)]
pub struct FileMove {
    /// Source file path
    pub from: PathBuf,
    /// Destination file path
    pub to: PathBuf,
}

/// File split pack recommendation
#[derive(Debug, Clone, Serialize)]
pub struct FileSplitPack {
    /// Type identifier
    pub kind: String,
    /// File path to split
    pub file: PathBuf,
    /// Reasons for splitting
    pub reasons: Vec&lt;String&gt;,
    /// Suggested split files
    pub suggested_splits: Vec&lt;SuggestedSplit&gt;,
    /// Value metrics
    pub value: SplitValue,
    /// Effort estimation
    pub effort: SplitEffort,
}

/// Suggested file split
#[derive(Debug, Clone, Serialize)]
pub struct SuggestedSplit {
    /// Name of the split file
    pub name: String,
    /// Entities (functions, classes) to move
    pub entities: Vec&lt;String&gt;,
    /// Lines of code in split
    pub loc: usize,
}

/// Value metrics for file splitting
#[derive(Debug, Clone, Serialize)]
pub struct SplitValue {
    /// Overall value score
    pub score: f64,
}

/// Effort estimation for file splitting
#[derive(Debug, Clone, Serialize)]
pub struct SplitEffort {
    /// Number of exports that need updating
    pub exports: usize,
    /// Number of external importers affected
    pub external_importers: usize,
}

/// Internal dependency graph for partitioning
pub type DependencyGraph = Graph&lt;FileNode, DependencyEdge, Directed&gt;;

/// File node in dependency graph
#[derive(Debug, Clone)]
pub struct FileNode {
    /// File path
    pub path: PathBuf,
    /// Lines of code
    pub loc: usize,
    /// File size in bytes
    pub size_bytes: usize,
}

/// Dependency edge in graph
#[derive(Debug, Clone)]
pub struct DependencyEdge {
    /// Weight (import count)
    pub weight: usize,
    /// Import type/relationship
    pub relationship_type: String,
}

/// Entity cohesion graph for file splitting
pub type CohesionGraph = Graph&lt;EntityNode, CohesionEdge, Undirected&gt;;

/// Entity node in cohesion graph
#[derive(Debug, Clone)]
pub struct EntityNode {
    /// Entity name (function, class, etc.)
    pub name: String,
    /// Entity type (function, class, etc.)
    pub entity_type: String,
    /// Lines of code for entity
    pub loc: usize,
    /// Referenced symbols/identifiers
    pub symbols: HashSet&lt;String&gt;,
}

/// Cohesion edge between entities
#[derive(Debug, Clone)]
pub struct CohesionEdge {
    /// Similarity weight (0.0 to 1.0)
    pub similarity: f64,
    /// Number of shared symbols
    pub shared_symbols: usize,
}

/// Import statement for dependency analysis
#[derive(Debug, Clone)]
pub struct ImportStatement {
    /// Module being imported
    pub module: String,
    /// Specific imports (None for star imports)
    pub imports: Option&lt;Vec&lt;String&gt;&gt;,
    /// Import type (default, named, star, etc.)
    pub import_type: String,
    /// Line number in file
    pub line_number: usize,
}
📄 src/core/pipeline/pipeline_config.rs
//! Configuration types and defaults for the analysis pipeline.

use serde::{Deserialize, Serialize};
use std::path::PathBuf;

use crate::core::config::ValknutConfig;

/// Configuration for comprehensive analysis
#[derive(Debug, Clone, Serialize, Deserialize)]
pub struct AnalysisConfig {
    /// Enable structure analysis
    pub enable_structure_analysis: bool,
    /// Enable complexity analysis
    pub enable_complexity_analysis: bool,
    /// Enable refactoring analysis
    pub enable_refactoring_analysis: bool,
    /// Enable impact analysis
    pub enable_impact_analysis: bool,
    /// Enable LSH-based clone detection
    pub enable_lsh_analysis: bool,
    /// Enable coverage analysis
    pub enable_coverage_analysis: bool,
    /// File extensions to include
    pub file_extensions: Vec&lt;String&gt;,
    /// Directories to exclude
    pub exclude_directories: Vec&lt;String&gt;,
    /// Maximum files to analyze (0 = no limit)
    pub max_files: usize,
}

impl Default for AnalysisConfig {
    fn default() -&gt; Self {
        Self {
            enable_structure_analysis: true,
            enable_complexity_analysis: true,
            enable_refactoring_analysis: true,
            enable_impact_analysis: true,
            enable_lsh_analysis: false,     // Disabled by default
            enable_coverage_analysis: true, // Enabled by default for comprehensive analysis
            file_extensions: vec![
                &quot;py&quot;.to_string(),
                &quot;js&quot;.to_string(),
                &quot;ts&quot;.to_string(),
                &quot;tsx&quot;.to_string(),
                &quot;jsx&quot;.to_string(),
                &quot;rs&quot;.to_string(),
                &quot;go&quot;.to_string(),
                &quot;java&quot;.to_string(),
            ],
            exclude_directories: vec![
                &quot;node_modules&quot;.to_string(),
                &quot;target&quot;.to_string(),
                &quot;__pycache__&quot;.to_string(),
                &quot;.git&quot;.to_string(),
                &quot;dist&quot;.to_string(),
                &quot;build&quot;.to_string(),
            ],
            max_files: 5000,
        }
    }
}

impl From&lt;ValknutConfig&gt; for AnalysisConfig {
    fn from(config: ValknutConfig) -&gt; Self {
        // Convert exclude patterns to directories - extract directory names from patterns
        let exclude_directories: Vec&lt;String&gt; = config
            .analysis
            .exclude_patterns
            .into_iter()
            .filter_map(|pattern| {
                // Extract directory names from patterns like &quot;*/node_modules/*&quot; -&gt; &quot;node_modules&quot;
                if pattern.contains(&#x27;/&#x27;) {
                    let trimmed = pattern.trim_start_matches(&quot;*/&quot;).trim_end_matches(&quot;/*&quot;);
                    if !trimmed.is_empty() &amp;&amp; !trimmed.contains(&#x27;*&#x27;) {
                        Some(trimmed.to_string())
                    } else {
                        None
                    }
                } else {
                    None
                }
            })
            .collect();

        // Derive file extensions from language config
        let file_extensions: Vec&lt;String&gt; = config
            .languages
            .values()
            .filter(|lang| lang.enabled)
            .flat_map(|lang| lang.file_extensions.clone())
            .map(|ext| ext.trim_start_matches(&#x27;.&#x27;).to_string()) // Remove leading dots
            .collect();

        let final_file_extensions = if file_extensions.is_empty() {
            vec![
                &quot;py&quot;.to_string(),
                &quot;js&quot;.to_string(),
                &quot;ts&quot;.to_string(),
                &quot;tsx&quot;.to_string(),
                &quot;jsx&quot;.to_string(),
                &quot;rs&quot;.to_string(),
                &quot;go&quot;.to_string(),
                &quot;java&quot;.to_string(),
            ]
        } else {
            file_extensions
        };

        let final_exclude_directories = if exclude_directories.is_empty() {
            vec![
                &quot;node_modules&quot;.to_string(),
                &quot;target&quot;.to_string(),
                &quot;__pycache__&quot;.to_string(),
                &quot;.git&quot;.to_string(),
                &quot;dist&quot;.to_string(),
                &quot;build&quot;.to_string(),
            ]
        } else {
            exclude_directories
        };

        Self {
            enable_structure_analysis: config.analysis.enable_structure_analysis,
            enable_complexity_analysis: true, // Default enabled, no equivalent in core config
            enable_refactoring_analysis: config.analysis.enable_refactoring_analysis,
            enable_impact_analysis: config.analysis.enable_graph_analysis, // Map graph analysis to impact analysis
            enable_lsh_analysis: config.analysis.enable_lsh_analysis,
            enable_coverage_analysis: config.analysis.enable_coverage_analysis,
            file_extensions: final_file_extensions,
            exclude_directories: final_exclude_directories,
            max_files: config.analysis.max_files,
        }
    }
}

/// Quality gate configuration for CI/CD integration
#[derive(Debug, Clone, Serialize, Deserialize)]
pub struct QualityGateConfig {
    /// Whether quality gates are enabled
    pub enabled: bool,
    /// Maximum allowed complexity score (0-100, lower is better)
    pub max_complexity_score: f64,
    /// Maximum allowed technical debt ratio (0-100, lower is better)
    pub max_technical_debt_ratio: f64,
    /// Minimum required maintainability score (0-100, higher is better)
    pub min_maintainability_score: f64,
    /// Maximum allowed critical issues
    pub max_critical_issues: usize,
    /// Maximum allowed high-priority issues
    pub max_high_priority_issues: usize,
}

impl Default for QualityGateConfig {
    fn default() -&gt; Self {
        Self {
            enabled: false,
            max_complexity_score: 70.0,
            max_technical_debt_ratio: 50.0,
            min_maintainability_score: 60.0,
            max_critical_issues: 5,
            max_high_priority_issues: 20,
        }
    }
}

/// Quality gate violation details
#[derive(Debug, Clone, Serialize, Deserialize)]
pub struct QualityGateViolation {
    /// Name of the violated rule
    pub rule_name: String,
    /// Description of the violation
    pub description: String,
    /// Current value that violated the threshold
    pub current_value: f64,
    /// The threshold that was violated
    pub threshold: f64,
    /// Severity of the violation
    pub severity: String,
    /// Files or components that contribute to this violation
    pub affected_files: Vec&lt;PathBuf&gt;,
    /// Recommended actions to fix this violation
    pub recommended_actions: Vec&lt;String&gt;,
}

/// Result of quality gate evaluation
#[derive(Debug, Clone, Serialize, Deserialize)]
pub struct QualityGateResult {
    /// Whether all quality gates passed
    pub passed: bool,
    /// List of violations (empty if all gates passed)
    pub violations: Vec&lt;QualityGateViolation&gt;,
    /// Overall quality score
    pub overall_score: f64,
}

pub use pipeline_results::{
    ComprehensiveAnalysisResult, AnalysisSummary, StructureAnalysisResults,

    CoverageAnalysisResults, HealthMetrics, PipelineResults, PipelineStatistics,

/// Additional tests for pipeline modules to improve coverage

#[cfg(test)]
mod tests {
    use super::*;
    use std::path::PathBuf;
    use tempfile::TempDir;
    use std::fs;
    
    #[tokio::test]
    async fn test_pipeline_fit_legacy_api() {
        let pipeline &amp;#x3D; AnalysisPipeline::default();
        let mut pipeline &amp;#x3D; pipeline;
        let result &amp;#x3D; pipeline.fit(&amp;amp;amp;[]).await;
        assert!(result.is_ok());
    }

    #[tokio::test]
    async fn test_pipeline_extractor_registry() {
        let pipeline &amp;#x3D; AnalysisPipeline::default();
        let registry &amp;#x3D; pipeline.extractor_registry();
        let extractors: Vec&amp;amp;lt;_&amp;amp;gt; &amp;#x3D; registry.get_all_extractors().collect();
        assert_eq!(extractors.len(), 0);
    }

    #[tokio::test]
    async fn test_pipeline_analyze_vectors_legacy() {
        let pipeline &amp;#x3D; AnalysisPipeline::default();
        let result &amp;#x3D; pipeline.analyze_vectors(vec![]).await;
        assert!(result.is_ok());
    }

    #[tokio::test]
    async fn test_pipeline_status() {
        let pipeline &amp;#x3D; AnalysisPipeline::default();
        let status &amp;#x3D; pipeline.get_status();
        assert!(status.ready);
        assert!(status.is_ready);
        assert!(status.config_valid);
    }

    #[tokio::test]
    async fn test_quality_gates_evaluation() {
        let pipeline &amp;#x3D; AnalysisPipeline::default();
        let config &amp;#x3D; QualityGateConfig::default();
        let results &amp;#x3D; pipeline_results::ComprehensiveAnalysisResult {
            analysis_id: &amp;amp;quot;test&amp;amp;quot;.to_string(),
            timestamp: chrono::Utc::now(),
            processing_time: 1.0,
            config: pipeline_config::AnalysisConfig::default(),
            summary: pipeline_results::AnalysisSummary {
                total_files: 1,
                total_entities: 1,
                total_lines_of_code: 100,
                languages: vec![&amp;amp;quot;Rust&amp;amp;quot;.to_string()],
                total_issues: 0,
                high_priority_issues: 0,
                critical_issues: 0,
            },
            structure: pipeline_results::StructureAnalysisResults {
                enabled: true,
                directory_recommendations: vec![],
                file_splitting_recommendations: vec![],
                issues_count: 0,
            },
            complexity: pipeline_results::ComplexityAnalysisResults {
                enabled: true,
                detailed_results: vec![],
                average_cyclomatic_complexity: 2.0,
                average_cognitive_complexity: 1.5,
                average_technical_debt_score: 10.0,
                average_maintainability_index: 85.0,
                issues_count: 0,
            },
            refactoring: pipeline_results::RefactoringAnalysisResults {
                enabled: true,
                detailed_results: vec![],
                opportunities_count: 0,
            },
            impact: pipeline_results::ImpactAnalysisResults {
                enabled: true,
                dependency_cycles: vec![],
                chokepoints: vec![],
                clone_groups: vec![],
                issues_count: 0,
            },
            lsh: pipeline_results::LshAnalysisResults {
                enabled: false,
                clone_pairs: vec![],

                avg_similarity: 0.0,
                duplicate_count: 0,

            coverage: pipeline_results::CoverageAnalysisResults {

    #[tokio::test]
    async fn test_analyze_directory_integration() {
        let temp_dir &amp;#x3D; TempDir::new().unwrap();
        let file_path &amp;#x3D; temp_dir.path().join(&amp;amp;quot;test.rs&amp;amp;quot;);
        fs::write(&amp;amp;amp;file_path, &amp;amp;quot;fn main() { println!(\&amp;amp;quot;Hello\&amp;amp;quot;); }&amp;amp;quot;).unwrap();
        
        let pipeline &amp;#x3D; AnalysisPipeline::default();
        let result &amp;#x3D; pipeline.analyze_directory(temp_dir.path()).await;
        assert!(result.is_ok());
    }

    #[tokio::test]
    async fn test_analyze_paths_with_progress() {
        let temp_dir &amp;#x3D; TempDir::new().unwrap();
        let file_path &amp;#x3D; temp_dir.path().join(&amp;amp;quot;test.rs&amp;amp;quot;);
        fs::write(&amp;amp;amp;file_path, &amp;amp;quot;fn main() { println!(\&amp;amp;quot;Hello\&amp;amp;quot;); }&amp;amp;quot;).unwrap();
        
        let pipeline &amp;#x3D; AnalysisPipeline::default();
        let paths &amp;#x3D; vec![temp_dir.path().to_path_buf()];
        
        let progress_called &amp;#x3D; std::sync::Arc::new(std::sync::atomic::AtomicBool::new(false));
        let progress_called_clone &amp;#x3D; progress_called.clone();
        let progress_callback &amp;#x3D; Some(Box::new(move |_msg: &amp;amp;amp;str, _progress: f64| {
            progress_called_clone.store(true, std::sync::atomic::Ordering::SeqCst);
        }) as ProgressCallback);
        
        let result &amp;#x3D; pipeline.analyze_paths(&amp;amp;amp;paths, progress_callback).await;
        assert!(result.is_ok());
        assert!(progress_called.load(std::sync::atomic::Ordering::SeqCst));
    }

        // Build hierarchical tree structure from flat file paths
        function buildTreeData(files) {
            if (!files || files.length === 0) {
                console.warn(&#x27;No files provided to buildTreeData&#x27;);
                return [];
            }
            
            const nodeMap = new Map();
            const rootNodes = [];
            
            files.forEach((file, index) =&gt; {
                const parts = file.path.split(&#x27;/&#x27;);
                let currentPath = &#x27;&#x27;;
                
                for (let i = 0; i &lt; parts.length; i++) {
                    const part = parts[i];
                    const parentPath = currentPath;
                    currentPath = currentPath ? `${currentPath}/${part}` : part;
                    const isLast = i === parts.length - 1;
                    
                    if (!nodeMap.has(currentPath)) {
                        const node = {
                            id: currentPath,
                            name: part,
                            isFolder: !isLast,
                            path: currentPath,
                            fileIndex: isLast ? index : undefined,
                            fileData: isLast ? file : undefined
                        };
                        
                        // Only add children array for folders
                        if (!isLast) {
                            node.children = [];
                        }
                        
                        nodeMap.set(currentPath, node);
                        
                        if (parentPath) {
                            const parent = nodeMap.get(parentPath);
                            if (parent &amp;&amp; parent.children) {
                                parent.children.push(node);
                            }
                        } else {
                            rootNodes.push(node);
                        }
                    }
                }
            });
            
            return rootNodes;
        }

        // Get file icon based on extension
        function getFileIcon(filename) {
            const ext = filename.split(&#x27;.&#x27;).pop().toLowerCase();
            switch (ext) {
                case &#x27;js&#x27;: case &#x27;jsx&#x27;: return &#x27;file-text&#x27;;
                case &#x27;ts&#x27;: case &#x27;tsx&#x27;: return &#x27;file-text&#x27;;
                case &#x27;py&#x27;: return &#x27;file-text&#x27;;
                case &#x27;rs&#x27;: return &#x27;file-text&#x27;;
                case &#x27;go&#x27;: return &#x27;file-text&#x27;;
                case &#x27;java&#x27;: return &#x27;file-text&#x27;;
                case &#x27;cpp&#x27;: case &#x27;c&#x27;: case &#x27;h&#x27;: return &#x27;file-text&#x27;;
                case &#x27;css&#x27;: return &#x27;file-text&#x27;;
                case &#x27;html&#x27;: return &#x27;file-text&#x27;;
                case &#x27;json&#x27;: return &#x27;file-text&#x27;;
                case &#x27;md&#x27;: return &#x27;file-text&#x27;;
                case &#x27;yml&#x27;: case &#x27;yaml&#x27;: return &#x27;file-text&#x27;;
                case &#x27;xml&#x27;: return &#x27;file-text&#x27;;
                case &#x27;sql&#x27;: return &#x27;file-text&#x27;;
                case &#x27;sh&#x27;: case &#x27;bash&#x27;: return &#x27;file-text&#x27;;
                case &#x27;dockerfile&#x27;: return &#x27;file-text&#x27;;
                case &#x27;gitignore&#x27;: return &#x27;file-text&#x27;;
                case &#x27;toml&#x27;: return &#x27;file-text&#x27;;
                case &#x27;lock&#x27;: return &#x27;file-text&#x27;;
                default: return &#x27;file-text&#x27;;
            }
        }

        // Tree Node Component
        function Node({ node, style, dragHandle, tree }) {
            const isFolder = node.isFolder;
            const isOpen = tree.isOpen(node.id);
            
            const handleClick = useCallback(() =&gt; {
                if (isFolder) {
                    tree.toggle(node.id);
                } else {
                    // Navigate to file section
                    const fileIndex = node.fileIndex;
                    if (fileIndex !== undefined) {
                        const element = document.getElementById(`file-${fileIndex + 1}`);
                        if (element) {
                            element.scrollIntoView({ behavior: &#x27;smooth&#x27;, block: &#x27;start&#x27; });
                        }
                    }
                }
            }, [node.id, isFolder, tree, node.fileIndex]);

            useEffect(() =&gt; {
                // Re-initialize Lucide icons for this node
                const iconElements = document.querySelectorAll(&#x27;[data-lucide]&#x27;);
                iconElements.forEach(el =&gt; {
                    if (!el.querySelector(&#x27;svg&#x27;)) {
                        lucide.createIcons();
                    }
                });
            });

            return (
                &lt;div 
                    ref={dragHandle} 
                    style={style} 
                    className=&quot;tree-node&quot;
                    onClick={handleClick}
                &gt;
                    &lt;div className=&quot;tree-node-content&quot;&gt;
                        {isFolder &amp;&amp; (
                            &lt;div className={`tree-arrow ${isOpen ? &#x27;expanded&#x27; : &#x27;&#x27;}`}&gt;
                                &lt;i data-lucide=&quot;chevron-right&quot; className=&quot;tree-icon&quot;&gt;&lt;/i&gt;
                            &lt;/div&gt;
                        )}
                        {!isFolder &amp;&amp; &lt;div className=&quot;tree-arrow&quot;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;}
                        
                        &lt;i 
                            data-lucide={isFolder ? &#x27;folder&#x27; : getFileIcon(node.name)} 
                            className={`tree-icon ${isFolder ? &#x27;folder-icon&#x27; : &#x27;file-icon&#x27;}`}
                        &gt;&lt;/i&gt;
                        
                        &lt;span className=&quot;tree-label&quot; title={node.path}&gt;
                            {node.name}
                        &lt;/span&gt;
                    &lt;/div&gt;
                &lt;/div&gt;
            );
        }

        // File Tree Component
        function FileTree() {
            const [treeData] = useState(() =&gt; {
                console.log(&#x27;Building tree data from:&#x27;, fileData);
                const tree = buildTreeData(fileData);
                console.log(&#x27;Built tree data:&#x27;, tree);
                return tree;
            });
            
            useEffect(() =&gt; {
                // Re-initialize Lucide icons after React renders
                const initIcons = () =&gt; {
                    try {
                        lucide.createIcons();
                        console.log(&#x27;Lucide icons initialized&#x27;);
                    } catch (error) {
                        console.error(&#x27;Error initializing Lucide icons:&#x27;, error);
                    }
                };
                
                // Initialize immediately and after a delay
                initIcons();
                setTimeout(initIcons, 100);
                setTimeout(initIcons, 500);
            }, []);

            if (!treeData || treeData.length === 0) {
                return (
                    &lt;div style={&amp;#123;&amp;#123; padding: &#x27;20px&#x27;, textAlign: &#x27;center&#x27;, color: &#x27;var(--text-muted)&#x27; &amp;#125;&amp;#125;}&gt;
                        No files to display
                    &lt;/div&gt;
                );
            }

            return (
                &lt;Tree
                    data={treeData}
                    openByDefault={false}
                    width=&quot;100%&quot;
                    height={400}
                    padding={25}
                    rowHeight={28}
                    indent={16}
                    overscanCount={8}
                &gt;
                    {Node}
                &lt;/Tree&gt;
            );
        }

        // Render the component
        try {
            const container = document.getElementById(&#x27;file-tree-container&#x27;);
            if (container) {
                const root = ReactDOM.createRoot(container);
                root.render(&lt;FileTree /&gt;);
                console.log(&#x27;React tree component rendered successfully&#x27;);
            } else {
                console.error(&#x27;Could not find file-tree-container element&#x27;);
            }
        } catch (error) {
            console.error(&#x27;Error rendering React tree:&#x27;, error);
        }
    &lt;/script&gt;
    &lt;script&gt;
        // Initialize Lucide icons
        lucide.createIcons();
    &lt;/script&gt;

pub use pipeline_results::{
    ComprehensiveAnalysisResult, AnalysisSummary, StructureAnalysisResults,
    ComplexityAnalysisResults, RefactoringAnalysisResults, ImpactAnalysisResults,
    CoverageAnalysisResults, HealthMetrics, PipelineResults, PipelineStatistics, 
    MemoryStats, ResultSummary, ScoringResults, FileScore, PipelineStatus

/// Additional tests for pipeline modules to improve coverage

#[cfg(test)]
mod tests {
    use super::*;
    use std::path::PathBuf;
    use tempfile::TempDir;
    use std::fs;
    
    #[tokio::test]
    async fn test_pipeline_fit_legacy_api() {
        let pipeline &amp;#x3D; AnalysisPipeline::default();
        let mut pipeline &amp;#x3D; pipeline;
        let result &amp;#x3D; pipeline.fit(&amp;amp;amp;[]).await;
        assert!(result.is_ok());
    }

    #[tokio::test]
    async fn test_pipeline_extractor_registry() {
        let pipeline &amp;#x3D; AnalysisPipeline::default();
        let registry &amp;#x3D; pipeline.extractor_registry();
        let extractors: Vec&amp;amp;lt;_&amp;amp;gt; &amp;#x3D; registry.get_all_extractors().collect();
        assert_eq!(extractors.len(), 0);
    }

    #[tokio::test]
    async fn test_pipeline_analyze_vectors_legacy() {
        let pipeline &amp;#x3D; AnalysisPipeline::default();
        let result &amp;#x3D; pipeline.analyze_vectors(vec![]).await;
        assert!(result.is_ok());
    }

    #[tokio::test]
    async fn test_pipeline_status() {
        let pipeline &amp;#x3D; AnalysisPipeline::default();
        let status &amp;#x3D; pipeline.get_status();
        assert!(status.ready);
        assert!(status.is_ready);
        assert!(status.config_valid);
    }

    #[tokio::test]
    async fn test_quality_gates_evaluation() {
        let pipeline &amp;#x3D; AnalysisPipeline::default();
        let config &amp;#x3D; QualityGateConfig::default();
        let results &amp;#x3D; pipeline_results::ComprehensiveAnalysisResult {
            analysis_id: &amp;amp;quot;test&amp;amp;quot;.to_string(),
            timestamp: chrono::Utc::now(),
            processing_time: 1.0,
            config: pipeline_config::AnalysisConfig::default(),
            summary: pipeline_results::AnalysisSummary {
                total_files: 1,
                total_entities: 1,
                total_lines_of_code: 100,
                languages: vec![&amp;amp;quot;Rust&amp;amp;quot;.to_string()],
                total_issues: 0,
                high_priority_issues: 0,
                critical_issues: 0,
            },
            structure: pipeline_results::StructureAnalysisResults {
                enabled: true,
                directory_recommendations: vec![],
                file_splitting_recommendations: vec![],
                issues_count: 0,
            },
            complexity: pipeline_results::ComplexityAnalysisResults {
                enabled: true,
                detailed_results: vec![],
                average_cyclomatic_complexity: 2.0,
                average_cognitive_complexity: 1.5,
                average_technical_debt_score: 10.0,
                average_maintainability_index: 85.0,
                issues_count: 0,
            },
            refactoring: pipeline_results::RefactoringAnalysisResults {
                enabled: true,
                detailed_results: vec![],
                opportunities_count: 0,
            },
            impact: pipeline_results::ImpactAnalysisResults {
                enabled: true,
                dependency_cycles: vec![],
                chokepoints: vec![],
                clone_groups: vec![],
                issues_count: 0,
            },
            lsh: pipeline_results::LshAnalysisResults {
                enabled: false,
                clone_pairs: vec![],
                max_similarity: 0.0,
                avg_similarity: 0.0,
                duplicate_count: 0,
                denoising_enabled: false,
                tfidf_stats: None,
            },
            coverage: pipeline_results::CoverageAnalysisResults {
                enabled: false,
                coverage_files_used: vec![],
                coverage_gaps: vec![],
                gaps_count: 0,
                overall_coverage_percentage: None,
                analysis_method: &amp;amp;quot;none&amp;amp;quot;.to_string(),
            },
            health_metrics: pipeline_results::HealthMetrics {
                overall_health_score: 88.0,
                maintainability_score: 85.0,
                technical_debt_ratio: 10.0,
                complexity_score: 15.0,
                structure_quality_score: 90.0,
            },
        };

        let gate_result &amp;#x3D; pipeline.evaluate_quality_gates(&amp;amp;amp;config, &amp;amp;amp;results);
        assert!(gate_result.passed);
    }

    #[tokio::test]
    async fn test_analyze_directory_integration() {
        let temp_dir &amp;#x3D; TempDir::new().unwrap();
        let file_path &amp;#x3D; temp_dir.path().join(&amp;amp;quot;test.rs&amp;amp;quot;);
        fs::write(&amp;amp;amp;file_path, &amp;amp;quot;fn main() { println!(\&amp;amp;quot;Hello\&amp;amp;quot;); }&amp;amp;quot;).unwrap();
        
        let pipeline &amp;#x3D; AnalysisPipeline::default();
        let result &amp;#x3D; pipeline.analyze_directory(temp_dir.path()).await;
        assert!(result.is_ok());
    }

    #[tokio::test]
    async fn test_analyze_paths_with_progress() {
        let temp_dir &amp;#x3D; TempDir::new().unwrap();
        let file_path &amp;#x3D; temp_dir.path().join(&amp;amp;quot;test.rs&amp;amp;quot;);
        fs::write(&amp;amp;amp;file_path, &amp;amp;quot;fn main() { println!(\&amp;amp;quot;Hello\&amp;amp;quot;); }&amp;amp;quot;).unwrap();
        
        let pipeline &amp;#x3D; AnalysisPipeline::default();
        let paths &amp;#x3D; vec![temp_dir.path().to_path_buf()];
        
        let progress_called &amp;#x3D; std::sync::Arc::new(std::sync::atomic::AtomicBool::new(false));
        let progress_called_clone &amp;#x3D; progress_called.clone();
        let progress_callback &amp;#x3D; Some(Box::new(move |_msg: &amp;amp;amp;str, _progress: f64| {
            progress_called_clone.store(true, std::sync::atomic::Ordering::SeqCst);
        }) as ProgressCallback);
        
        let result &amp;#x3D; pipeline.analyze_paths(&amp;amp;amp;paths, progress_callback).await;
        assert!(result.is_ok());
        assert!(progress_called.load(std::sync::atomic::Ordering::SeqCst));
    }

            },
            {
                path: &quot;detectors/mod.rs&quot;,
                icon: &quot;file-code&quot;,
                index: 5,
                size: &quot;362 B&quot;,
                tokens: &quot;69&quot;,
                score: &quot;0.58&quot;
            },
            {
                path: &quot;io/mod.rs&quot;,
                icon: &quot;file-code&quot;,
                index: 6,
                size: &quot;96 B&quot;,
                tokens: &quot;20&quot;,
                score: &quot;0.56&quot;
            },
            {
                path: &quot;perf.data&quot;,
                icon: &quot;file&quot;,
                index: 7,
                size: &quot;0 B&quot;,
                tokens: &quot;0&quot;,
                score: &quot;0.10&quot;
            }
        ];

        // Build hierarchical tree structure from flat file paths
        function buildTreeData(files) {
            if (!files || files.length === 0) {
                console.warn(&#x27;No files provided to buildTreeData&#x27;);
                return [];
            }
            
            const nodeMap = new Map();
            const rootNodes = [];
            
            files.forEach((file, index) =&gt; {
                const parts = file.path.split(&#x27;/&#x27;);
                let currentPath = &#x27;&#x27;;
                
                for (let i = 0; i &lt; parts.length; i++) {
                    const part = parts[i];
                    const parentPath = currentPath;
                    currentPath = currentPath ? `${currentPath}/${part}` : part;
                    const isLast = i === parts.length - 1;
                    
                    if (!nodeMap.has(currentPath)) {
                        const node = {
                            id: currentPath,
                            name: part,
                            isFolder: !isLast,
                            path: currentPath,
                            fileIndex: isLast ? index : undefined,
                            fileData: isLast ? file : undefined
                        };
                        
                        // Only add children array for folders
                        if (!isLast) {
                            node.children = [];
                        }
                        
                        nodeMap.set(currentPath, node);
                        
                        if (parentPath) {
                            const parent = nodeMap.get(parentPath);
                            if (parent &amp;&amp; parent.children) {
                                parent.children.push(node);
                            }
                        } else {
                            rootNodes.push(node);
                        }
                    }
                }
            });
            
            return rootNodes;
        }

        // Get file icon based on extension
        function getFileIcon(filename) {
            const ext = filename.split(&#x27;.&#x27;).pop().toLowerCase();
            switch (ext) {
                case &#x27;js&#x27;: case &#x27;jsx&#x27;: return &#x27;file-text&#x27;;
                case &#x27;ts&#x27;: case &#x27;tsx&#x27;: return &#x27;file-text&#x27;;
                case &#x27;py&#x27;: return &#x27;file-text&#x27;;
                case &#x27;rs&#x27;: return &#x27;file-text&#x27;;
                case &#x27;go&#x27;: return &#x27;file-text&#x27;;
                case &#x27;java&#x27;: return &#x27;file-text&#x27;;
                case &#x27;cpp&#x27;: case &#x27;c&#x27;: case &#x27;h&#x27;: return &#x27;file-text&#x27;;
                case &#x27;css&#x27;: return &#x27;file-text&#x27;;
                case &#x27;html&#x27;: return &#x27;file-text&#x27;;
                case &#x27;json&#x27;: return &#x27;file-text&#x27;;
                case &#x27;md&#x27;: return &#x27;file-text&#x27;;
                case &#x27;yml&#x27;: case &#x27;yaml&#x27;: return &#x27;file-text&#x27;;
                case &#x27;xml&#x27;: return &#x27;file-text&#x27;;
                case &#x27;sql&#x27;: return &#x27;file-text&#x27;;
                case &#x27;sh&#x27;: case &#x27;bash&#x27;: return &#x27;file-text&#x27;;
                case &#x27;dockerfile&#x27;: return &#x27;file-text&#x27;;
                case &#x27;gitignore&#x27;: return &#x27;file-text&#x27;;
                case &#x27;toml&#x27;: return &#x27;file-text&#x27;;
                case &#x27;lock&#x27;: return &#x27;file-text&#x27;;
                default: return &#x27;file-text&#x27;;
            }
        }

        // Tree Node Component
        function Node({ node, style, dragHandle, tree }) {
            const isFolder = node.isFolder;
            const isOpen = tree.isOpen(node.id);
            
            const handleClick = useCallback(() =&gt; {
                if (isFolder) {
                    tree.toggle(node.id);
                } else {
                    // Navigate to file section
                    const fileIndex = node.fileIndex;
                    if (fileIndex !== undefined) {
                        const element = document.getElementById(`file-${fileIndex + 1}`);
                        if (element) {
                            element.scrollIntoView({ behavior: &#x27;smooth&#x27;, block: &#x27;start&#x27; });
                        }
                    }
                }
            }, [node.id, isFolder, tree, node.fileIndex]);

            useEffect(() =&gt; {
                // Re-initialize Lucide icons for this node
                const iconElements = document.querySelectorAll(&#x27;[data-lucide]&#x27;);
                iconElements.forEach(el =&gt; {
                    if (!el.querySelector(&#x27;svg&#x27;)) {
                        lucide.createIcons();
                    }
                });
            });

            return (
                &lt;div 
                    ref={dragHandle} 
                    style={style} 
                    className=&quot;tree-node&quot;
                    onClick={handleClick}
                &gt;
                    &lt;div className=&quot;tree-node-content&quot;&gt;
                        {isFolder &amp;&amp; (
                            &lt;div className={`tree-arrow ${isOpen ? &#x27;expanded&#x27; : &#x27;&#x27;}`}&gt;
                                &lt;i data-lucide=&quot;chevron-right&quot; className=&quot;tree-icon&quot;&gt;&lt;/i&gt;
                            &lt;/div&gt;
                        )}
                        {!isFolder &amp;&amp; &lt;div className=&quot;tree-arrow&quot;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;}
                        
                        &lt;i 
                            data-lucide={isFolder ? &#x27;folder&#x27; : getFileIcon(node.name)} 
                            className={`tree-icon ${isFolder ? &#x27;folder-icon&#x27; : &#x27;file-icon&#x27;}`}
                        &gt;&lt;/i&gt;
                        
                        &lt;span className=&quot;tree-label&quot; title={node.path}&gt;
                            {node.name}
                        &lt;/span&gt;
                    &lt;/div&gt;
                &lt;/div&gt;
            );
        }

        // File Tree Component
        function FileTree() {
            const [treeData] = useState(() =&gt; {
                console.log(&#x27;Building tree data from:&#x27;, fileData);
                const tree = buildTreeData(fileData);
                console.log(&#x27;Built tree data:&#x27;, tree);
                return tree;
            });
            
            useEffect(() =&gt; {
                // Re-initialize Lucide icons after React renders
                const initIcons = () =&gt; {
                    try {
                        lucide.createIcons();
                        console.log(&#x27;Lucide icons initialized&#x27;);
                    } catch (error) {
                        console.error(&#x27;Error initializing Lucide icons:&#x27;, error);
                    }
                };
                
                // Initialize immediately and after a delay
                initIcons();
                setTimeout(initIcons, 100);
                setTimeout(initIcons, 500);
            }, []);

            if (!treeData || treeData.length === 0) {
                return (
                    &lt;div style={&amp;#123;&amp;#123; padding: &#x27;20px&#x27;, textAlign: &#x27;center&#x27;, color: &#x27;var(--text-muted)&#x27; &amp;#125;&amp;#125;}&gt;
                        No files to display
                    &lt;/div&gt;
                );
            }

            return (
                &lt;Tree
                    data={treeData}
                    openByDefault={false}
                    width=&quot;100%&quot;
                    height={400}
                    padding={25}
                    rowHeight={28}
                    indent={16}
                    overscanCount={8}
                &gt;
                    {Node}
                &lt;/Tree&gt;
            );
        }

        // Render the component
        try {
            const container = document.getElementById(&#x27;file-tree-container&#x27;);
            if (container) {
                const root = ReactDOM.createRoot(container);
                root.render(&lt;FileTree /&gt;);
                console.log(&#x27;React tree component rendered successfully&#x27;);
            } else {
                console.error(&#x27;Could not find file-tree-container element&#x27;);
            }
        } catch (error) {
            console.error(&#x27;Error rendering React tree:&#x27;, error);
        }
    &lt;/script&gt;
    &lt;script&gt;
        // Initialize Lucide icons
        lucide.createIcons();
    &lt;/script&gt;

    #[tokio::test]
    async fn test_analyze_paths_with_progress() {
        let temp_dir &amp;#x3D; TempDir::new().unwrap();
        let file_path &amp;#x3D; temp_dir.path().join(&amp;amp;quot;test.rs&amp;amp;quot;);
        fs::write(&amp;amp;amp;file_path, &amp;amp;quot;fn main() { println!(\&amp;amp;quot;Hello\&amp;amp;quot;); }&amp;amp;quot;).unwrap();
        
        let pipeline &amp;#x3D; AnalysisPipeline::default();
        let paths &amp;#x3D; vec![temp_dir.path().to_path_buf()];
        
        let progress_called &amp;#x3D; std::sync::Arc::new(std::sync::atomic::AtomicBool::new(false));
        let progress_called_clone &amp;#x3D; progress_called.clone();
        let progress_callback &amp;#x3D; Some(Box::new(move |_msg: &amp;amp;amp;str, _progress: f64| {
            progress_called_clone.store(true, std::sync::atomic::Ordering::SeqCst);
        }) as ProgressCallback);
        
        let result &amp;#x3D; pipeline.analyze_paths(&amp;amp;amp;paths, progress_callback).await;
        assert!(result.is_ok());
        assert!(progress_called.load(std::sync::atomic::Ordering::SeqCst));
    }

        const { useState, useCallback, useEffect } = React;
