📄 vscode-extension/src/analyzer.ts
import * as vscode from &#x27;vscode&#x27;;
import * as cp from &#x27;child_process&#x27;;
import * as path from &#x27;path&#x27;;
import * as fs from &#x27;fs&#x27;;

export interface AnalyzeOptions {
    onProgress?: (message: string) =&gt; void;
    cancellationToken?: vscode.CancellationToken;
}

export class ValknutAnalyzer {
    private config = vscode.workspace.getConfiguration(&#x27;valknut&#x27;);

    async analyzeWorkspace(workspacePath: string, options: AnalyzeOptions = {}): Promise&lt;string | null&gt; {
        const executablePath = this.config.get&lt;string&gt;(&#x27;executablePath&#x27;, &#x27;valknut&#x27;);
        const reportDir = path.join(workspacePath, &#x27;reports&#x27;);
        const reportFile = path.join(reportDir, `valknut-report-${Date.now()}.json`);

        // Ensure reports directory exists
        if (!fs.existsSync(reportDir)) {
            fs.mkdirSync(reportDir, { recursive: true });
        }

        return new Promise((resolve, reject) =&gt; {
            options.onProgress?.(&#x27;Starting Valknut analysis...&#x27;);

            const args = [
                &#x27;analyze&#x27;,
                workspacePath,
                &#x27;--output&#x27;, reportFile,
                &#x27;--format&#x27;, &#x27;json&#x27;
            ];

            const process = cp.spawn(executablePath, args, {
                cwd: workspacePath,
                stdio: [&#x27;ignore&#x27;, &#x27;pipe&#x27;, &#x27;pipe&#x27;]
            });

            let stdout = &#x27;&#x27;;
            let stderr = &#x27;&#x27;;

            process.stdout?.on(&#x27;data&#x27;, (data: Buffer) =&gt; {
                const output = data.toString();
                stdout += output;
                
                // Parse progress messages if any
                const lines = output.split(&#x27;\n&#x27;).filter(line =&gt; line.trim());
                for (const line of lines) {
                    if (line.includes(&#x27;Analyzing&#x27;) || line.includes(&#x27;Processing&#x27;)) {
                        options.onProgress?.(line.trim());
                    }
                }
            });

            process.stderr?.on(&#x27;data&#x27;, (data: Buffer) =&gt; {
                stderr += data.toString();
            });

            process.on(&#x27;close&#x27;, (code) =&gt; {
                if (options.cancellationToken?.isCancellationRequested) {
                    reject(new Error(&#x27;Analysis cancelled&#x27;));
                    return;
                }

                if (code === 0) {
                    // Check if report file was created
                    if (fs.existsSync(reportFile)) {
                        options.onProgress?.(&#x27;Analysis completed successfully&#x27;);
                        resolve(reportFile);
                    } else {
                        reject(new Error(&#x27;Analysis completed but no report was generated&#x27;));
                    }
                } else {
                    reject(new Error(`Analysis failed with code ${code}: ${stderr || stdout}`));
                }
            });

            process.on(&#x27;error&#x27;, (error) =&gt; {
                reject(new Error(`Failed to start Valknut: ${error.message}`));
            });

            // Handle cancellation
            options.cancellationToken?.onCancellationRequested(() =&gt; {
                process.kill();
            });
        });
    }

    async analyzeFile(filePath: string, options: AnalyzeOptions = {}): Promise&lt;string | null&gt; {
        const executablePath = this.config.get&lt;string&gt;(&#x27;executablePath&#x27;, &#x27;valknut&#x27;);
        const workspaceRoot = vscode.workspace.getWorkspaceFolder(vscode.Uri.file(filePath))?.uri.fsPath;
        
        if (!workspaceRoot) {
            throw new Error(&#x27;File is not in a workspace&#x27;);
        }

        const reportDir = path.join(workspaceRoot, &#x27;reports&#x27;);
        const reportFile = path.join(reportDir, `valknut-file-${Date.now()}.json`);

        // Ensure reports directory exists
        if (!fs.existsSync(reportDir)) {
            fs.mkdirSync(reportDir, { recursive: true });
        }

        return new Promise((resolve, reject) =&gt; {
            options.onProgress?.(&#x27;Analyzing file...&#x27;);

            const args = [
                &#x27;analyze&#x27;,
                filePath,
                &#x27;--output&#x27;, reportFile,
                &#x27;--format&#x27;, &#x27;json&#x27;
            ];

            const process = cp.spawn(executablePath, args, {
                cwd: workspaceRoot,
                stdio: [&#x27;ignore&#x27;, &#x27;pipe&#x27;, &#x27;pipe&#x27;]
            });

            let stdout = &#x27;&#x27;;
            let stderr = &#x27;&#x27;;

            process.stdout?.on(&#x27;data&#x27;, (data: Buffer) =&gt; {
                stdout += data.toString();
            });

            process.stderr?.on(&#x27;data&#x27;, (data: Buffer) =&gt; {
                stderr += data.toString();
            });

            process.on(&#x27;close&#x27;, (code) =&gt; {
                if (options.cancellationToken?.isCancellationRequested) {
                    reject(new Error(&#x27;Analysis cancelled&#x27;));
                    return;
                }

                if (code === 0) {
                    if (fs.existsSync(reportFile)) {
                        options.onProgress?.(&#x27;File analysis completed&#x27;);
                        resolve(reportFile);
                    } else {
                        reject(new Error(&#x27;Analysis completed but no report was generated&#x27;));
                    }
                } else {
                    reject(new Error(`Analysis failed with code ${code}: ${stderr || stdout}`));
                }
            });

            process.on(&#x27;error&#x27;, (error) =&gt; {
                if (error.message.includes(&#x27;ENOENT&#x27;)) {
                    reject(new Error(`Valknut executable not found at &#x27;${executablePath}&#x27;. Please check the &#x27;valknut.executablePath&#x27; setting.`));
                } else {
                    reject(new Error(`Failed to start Valknut: ${error.message}`));
                }
            });

            // Handle cancellation
            options.cancellationToken?.onCancellationRequested(() =&gt; {
                process.kill();
            });
        });
    }

    async isValknutAvailable(): Promise&lt;boolean&gt; {
        const executablePath = this.config.get&lt;string&gt;(&#x27;executablePath&#x27;, &#x27;valknut&#x27;);

        return new Promise((resolve) =&gt; {
            const process = cp.spawn(executablePath, [&#x27;--version&#x27;], {
                stdio: &#x27;ignore&#x27;
            });

            process.on(&#x27;close&#x27;, (code) =&gt; {
                resolve(code === 0);
            });

            process.on(&#x27;error&#x27;, () =&gt; {
                resolve(false);
            });
        });
    }

    async getVersion(): Promise&lt;string | null&gt; {
        const executablePath = this.config.get&lt;string&gt;(&#x27;executablePath&#x27;, &#x27;valknut&#x27;);

        return new Promise((resolve) =&gt; {
            const process = cp.spawn(executablePath, [&#x27;--version&#x27;], {
                stdio: [&#x27;ignore&#x27;, &#x27;pipe&#x27;, &#x27;ignore&#x27;]
            });

            let version = &#x27;&#x27;;
            process.stdout?.on(&#x27;data&#x27;, (data: Buffer) =&gt; {
                version += data.toString().trim();
            });

            process.on(&#x27;close&#x27;, (code) =&gt; {
                if (code === 0 &amp;&amp; version) {
                    resolve(version);
                } else {
                    resolve(null);
                }
            });

            process.on(&#x27;error&#x27;, () =&gt; {
                resolve(null);
            });
        });
    }
}
📄 src/lang/rust_lang.rs.disabled
//! Rust language adapter with tree-sitter integration.

use std::collections::HashMap;

use serde_json::{self, Value};

use super::common::{EntityKind, ParsedEntity, ParseIndex, SourceLocation};
use crate::core::errors::{Result, ValknutError};
use crate::core::featureset::CodeEntity;

/// Rust-specific parsing and analysis
pub struct RustAdapter {
    /// Tree-sitter parser for Rust
    parser: Parser,
    
    /// Language instance
    language: Language,
}

impl RustAdapter {
    /// Create a new Rust adapter
    pub fn new() -&gt; Result&lt;Self&gt; {
        // Simple test to verify tree_sitter_rust access
        let language = match std::panic::catch_unwind(|| tree_sitter_rust::language()) {
            Ok(lang) =&gt; lang,
            Err(_) =&gt; return Err(ValknutError::parse(&quot;rust&quot;, &quot;Failed to access tree_sitter_rust::language()&quot;.to_string())),
        };
        
        let mut parser = Parser::new();
        parser.set_language(language)
            .map_err(|e| ValknutError::parse(&quot;rust&quot;, format!(&quot;Failed to set Rust language: {:?}&quot;, e)))?;
        
        Ok(Self { parser, language })
    }
    
    /// Parse Rust source code and extract entities
    pub fn parse_source(&amp;mut self, source_code: &amp;str, file_path: &amp;str) -&gt; Result&lt;ParseIndex&gt; {
        let tree = self.parser.parse(source_code, None)
            .ok_or_else(|| ValknutError::parse(&quot;rust&quot;, &quot;Failed to parse Rust source code&quot;))?;
        
        let mut index = ParseIndex::new();
        let mut entity_id_counter = 0;
        
        // Walk the tree and extract entities
        self.extract_entities_recursive(
            tree.root_node(), 
            source_code, 
            file_path, 
            None, 
            &amp;mut index, 
            &amp;mut entity_id_counter
        )?;
        
        Ok(index)
    }
    
    /// Extract entities from Rust code and convert to CodeEntity format
    pub fn extract_code_entities(&amp;mut self, source_code: &amp;str, file_path: &amp;str) -&gt; Result&lt;Vec&lt;CodeEntity&gt;&gt; {
        let parse_index = self.parse_source(source_code, file_path)?;
        let mut code_entities = Vec::new();
        
        for entity in parse_index.entities.values() {
            let code_entity = self.convert_to_code_entity(entity, source_code)?;
            code_entities.push(code_entity);
        }
        
        Ok(code_entities)
    }
    
    /// Recursively extract entities from the AST
    fn extract_entities_recursive(
        &amp;self,
        node: Node,
        source_code: &amp;str,
        file_path: &amp;str,
        parent_id: Option&lt;String&gt;,
        index: &amp;mut ParseIndex,
        entity_id_counter: &amp;mut usize,
    ) -&gt; Result&lt;()&gt; {
        // Check if this node represents an entity we care about
        if let Some(entity) = self.node_to_entity(node, source_code, file_path, parent_id.clone(), entity_id_counter)? {
            let entity_id = entity.id.clone();
            index.add_entity(entity);
            
            // Process child nodes with this entity as parent
            let mut cursor = node.walk();
            for child in node.children(&amp;mut cursor) {
                self.extract_entities_recursive(
                    child, 
                    source_code, 
                    file_path, 
                    Some(entity_id.clone()), 
                    index, 
                    entity_id_counter
                )?;
            }
        } else {
            // Process child nodes with current parent
            let mut cursor = node.walk();
            for child in node.children(&amp;mut cursor) {
                self.extract_entities_recursive(
                    child, 
                    source_code, 
                    file_path, 
                    parent_id.clone(), 
                    index, 
                    entity_id_counter
                )?;
            }
        }
        
        Ok(())
    }
    
    /// Convert a tree-sitter node to a ParsedEntity if it represents an entity
    fn node_to_entity(
        &amp;self,
        node: Node,
        source_code: &amp;str,
        file_path: &amp;str,
        parent_id: Option&lt;String&gt;,
        entity_id_counter: &amp;mut usize,
    ) -&gt; Result&lt;Option&lt;ParsedEntity&gt;&gt; {
        let entity_kind = match node.kind() {
            &quot;function_item&quot; =&gt; EntityKind::Function,
            &quot;impl_item&quot; =&gt; return Ok(None), // Skip impl blocks themselves
            &quot;struct_item&quot; =&gt; EntityKind::Struct,
            &quot;enum_item&quot; =&gt; EntityKind::Enum,
            &quot;trait_item&quot; =&gt; EntityKind::Interface, // Treat traits as interfaces
            &quot;mod_item&quot; =&gt; EntityKind::Module,
            &quot;const_item&quot; =&gt; EntityKind::Constant,
            &quot;static_item&quot; =&gt; EntityKind::Constant,
            &quot;function_signature_item&quot; =&gt; EntityKind::Function, // Trait methods
            _ =&gt; return Ok(None),
        };
        
        let name = self.extract_name(&amp;node, source_code)?
            .ok_or_else(|| ValknutError::parse(&quot;rust&quot;, &quot;Could not extract entity name&quot;))?;
        
        *entity_id_counter += 1;
        let entity_id = format!(&quot;{}:{}:{}&quot;, file_path, entity_kind as u8, *entity_id_counter);
        
        let location = SourceLocation {
            file_path: file_path.to_string(),
            start_line: node.start_position().row + 1,
            end_line: node.end_position().row + 1,
            start_column: node.start_position().column + 1,
            end_column: node.end_position().column + 1,
        };
        
        let mut metadata = HashMap::new();
        
        // Add Rust-specific metadata
        metadata.insert(&quot;node_kind&quot;.to_string(), Value::String(node.kind().to_string()));
        metadata.insert(&quot;byte_range&quot;.to_string(), serde_json::json!([node.start_byte(), node.end_byte()]));
        
        // Extract additional metadata based on entity type
        match entity_kind {
            EntityKind::Function =&gt; {
                self.extract_function_metadata(&amp;node, source_code, &amp;mut metadata)?;
            }
            EntityKind::Struct =&gt; {
                self.extract_struct_metadata(&amp;node, source_code, &amp;mut metadata)?;
            }
            EntityKind::Enum =&gt; {
                self.extract_enum_metadata(&amp;node, source_code, &amp;mut metadata)?;
            }
            EntityKind::Interface =&gt; { // trait
                self.extract_trait_metadata(&amp;node, source_code, &amp;mut metadata)?;
            }
            EntityKind::Module =&gt; {
                self.extract_module_metadata(&amp;node, source_code, &amp;mut metadata)?;
            }
            _ =&gt; {}
        }
        
        let entity = ParsedEntity {
            id: entity_id,
            kind: entity_kind,
            name,
            parent: parent_id,
            children: Vec::new(), // Will be populated later
            location,
            metadata,
        };
        
        Ok(Some(entity))
    }
    
    /// Extract the name of an entity from its AST node
    fn extract_name(&amp;self, node: &amp;Node, source_code: &amp;str) -&gt; Result&lt;Option&lt;String&gt;&gt; {
        let mut cursor = node.walk();
        
        match node.kind() {
            &quot;function_item&quot; | &quot;struct_item&quot; | &quot;enum_item&quot; | &quot;trait_item&quot; | &quot;mod_item&quot; 
            | &quot;const_item&quot; | &quot;static_item&quot; | &quot;function_signature_item&quot; =&gt; {
                // Look for the identifier child
                for child in node.children(&amp;mut cursor) {
                    if child.kind() == &quot;identifier&quot; {
                        return Ok(Some(child.utf8_text(source_code.as_bytes())?.to_string()));
                    } else if child.kind() == &quot;type_identifier&quot; {
                        return Ok(Some(child.utf8_text(source_code.as_bytes())?.to_string()));
                    }
                }
            }
            _ =&gt; {}
        }
        
        Ok(None)
    }
    
    /// Extract function-specific metadata
    fn extract_function_metadata(&amp;self, node: &amp;Node, source_code: &amp;str, metadata: &amp;mut HashMap&lt;String, Value&gt;) -&gt; Result&lt;()&gt; {
        let mut cursor = node.walk();
        let mut parameters = Vec::new();
        let mut is_async = false;
        let mut is_unsafe = false;
        let mut is_const = false;
        let mut return_type = None;
        let mut visibility = &quot;private&quot;.to_string();
        
        for child in node.children(&amp;mut cursor) {
            match child.kind() {
                &quot;parameters&quot; =&gt; {
                    // Extract parameter information
                    let mut param_cursor = child.walk();
                    for param_child in child.children(&amp;mut param_cursor) {
                        if param_child.kind() == &quot;parameter&quot; {
                            let mut inner_cursor = param_child.walk();
                            for inner_child in param_child.children(&amp;mut inner_cursor) {
                                if inner_child.kind() == &quot;identifier&quot; {
                                    let param_name = inner_child.utf8_text(source_code.as_bytes())?;
                                    parameters.push(param_name);
                                    break;
                                }
                            }
                        }
                    }
                }
                &quot;async&quot; =&gt; {
                    is_async = true;
                }
                &quot;unsafe&quot; =&gt; {
                    is_unsafe = true;
                }
                &quot;const&quot; =&gt; {
                    is_const = true;
                }
                &quot;visibility_modifier&quot; =&gt; {
                    let vis_text = child.utf8_text(source_code.as_bytes())?;
                    visibility = vis_text.to_string();
                }
                _ =&gt; {
                    // Check for return type in function signature
                    if child.kind().contains(&quot;type&quot;) {
                        return_type = Some(child.utf8_text(source_code.as_bytes())?.to_string());
                    }
                }
            }
        }
        
        metadata.insert(&quot;parameters&quot;.to_string(), serde_json::json!(parameters));
        metadata.insert(&quot;is_async&quot;.to_string(), Value::Bool(is_async));
        metadata.insert(&quot;is_unsafe&quot;.to_string(), Value::Bool(is_unsafe));
        metadata.insert(&quot;is_const&quot;.to_string(), Value::Bool(is_const));
        metadata.insert(&quot;visibility&quot;.to_string(), Value::String(visibility));
        if let Some(ret_type) = return_type {
            metadata.insert(&quot;return_type&quot;.to_string(), Value::String(ret_type));
        }
        
        Ok(())
    }
    
    /// Extract struct-specific metadata
    fn extract_struct_metadata(&amp;self, node: &amp;Node, source_code: &amp;str, metadata: &amp;mut HashMap&lt;String, Value&gt;) -&gt; Result&lt;()&gt; {
        let mut cursor = node.walk();
        let mut fields = Vec::new();
        let mut visibility = &quot;private&quot;.to_string();
        let mut generic_params = Vec::new();
        
        for child in node.children(&amp;mut cursor) {
            match child.kind() {
                &quot;field_declaration_list&quot; =&gt; {
                    let mut field_cursor = child.walk();
                    for field_child in child.children(&amp;mut field_cursor) {
                        if field_child.kind() == &quot;field_declaration&quot; {
                            let mut inner_cursor = field_child.walk();
                            for inner_child in field_child.children(&amp;mut inner_cursor) {
                                if inner_child.kind() == &quot;field_identifier&quot; {
                                    let field_name = inner_child.utf8_text(source_code.as_bytes())?;
                                    fields.push(field_name);
                                }
                            }
                        }
                    }
                }
                &quot;visibility_modifier&quot; =&gt; {
                    let vis_text = child.utf8_text(source_code.as_bytes())?;
                    visibility = vis_text.to_string();
                }
                &quot;type_parameters&quot; =&gt; {
                    let mut param_cursor = child.walk();
                    for param_child in child.children(&amp;mut param_cursor) {
                        if param_child.kind() == &quot;type_identifier&quot; {
                            let param_name = param_child.utf8_text(source_code.as_bytes())?;
                            generic_params.push(param_name);
                        }
                    }
                }
                _ =&gt; {}
            }
        }
        
        metadata.insert(&quot;fields&quot;.to_string(), serde_json::json!(fields));
        metadata.insert(&quot;visibility&quot;.to_string(), Value::String(visibility));
        if !generic_params.is_empty() {
            metadata.insert(&quot;generic_parameters&quot;.to_string(), serde_json::json!(generic_params));
        }
        
        Ok(())
    }
    
    /// Extract enum-specific metadata
    fn extract_enum_metadata(&amp;self, node: &amp;Node, source_code: &amp;str, metadata: &amp;mut HashMap&lt;String, Value&gt;) -&gt; Result&lt;()&gt; {
        let mut cursor = node.walk();
        let mut variants = Vec::new();
        let mut visibility = &quot;private&quot;.to_string();
        
        for child in node.children(&amp;mut cursor) {
            match child.kind() {
                &quot;enum_variant_list&quot; =&gt; {
                    let mut variant_cursor = child.walk();
                    for variant_child in child.children(&amp;mut variant_cursor) {
                        if variant_child.kind() == &quot;enum_variant&quot; {
                            let mut inner_cursor = variant_child.walk();
                            for inner_child in variant_child.children(&amp;mut inner_cursor) {
                                if inner_child.kind() == &quot;identifier&quot; {
                                    let variant_name = inner_child.utf8_text(source_code.as_bytes())?;
                                    variants.push(variant_name);
                                    break;
                                }
                            }
                        }
                    }
                }
                &quot;visibility_modifier&quot; =&gt; {
                    let vis_text = child.utf8_text(source_code.as_bytes())?;
                    visibility = vis_text.to_string();
                }
                _ =&gt; {}
            }
        }
        
        metadata.insert(&quot;variants&quot;.to_string(), serde_json::json!(variants));
        metadata.insert(&quot;visibility&quot;.to_string(), Value::String(visibility));
        
        Ok(())
    }
    
    /// Extract trait-specific metadata
    fn extract_trait_metadata(&amp;self, node: &amp;Node, source_code: &amp;str, metadata: &amp;mut HashMap&lt;String, Value&gt;) -&gt; Result&lt;()&gt; {
        let mut cursor = node.walk();
        let mut methods = Vec::new();
        let mut visibility = &quot;private&quot;.to_string();
        let mut supertrait_bounds = Vec::new();
        
        for child in node.children(&amp;mut cursor) {
            match child.kind() {
                &quot;declaration_list&quot; =&gt; {
                    let mut method_cursor = child.walk();
                    for method_child in child.children(&amp;mut method_cursor) {
                        if method_child.kind() == &quot;function_signature_item&quot; {
                            let method_name = self.extract_name(&amp;method_child, source_code)?;
                            if let Some(name) = method_name {
                                methods.push(name);
                            }
                        }
                    }
                }
                &quot;visibility_modifier&quot; =&gt; {
                    let vis_text = child.utf8_text(source_code.as_bytes())?;
                    visibility = vis_text.to_string();
                }
                &quot;trait_bounds&quot; =&gt; {
                    let mut bounds_cursor = child.walk();
                    for bounds_child in child.children(&amp;mut bounds_cursor) {
                        if bounds_child.kind() == &quot;type_identifier&quot; {
                            let bound_name = bounds_child.utf8_text(source_code.as_bytes())?;
                            supertrait_bounds.push(bound_name);
                        }
                    }
                }
                _ =&gt; {}
            }
        }
        
        metadata.insert(&quot;methods&quot;.to_string(), serde_json::json!(methods));
        metadata.insert(&quot;visibility&quot;.to_string(), Value::String(visibility));
        if !supertrait_bounds.is_empty() {
            metadata.insert(&quot;supertrait_bounds&quot;.to_string(), serde_json::json!(supertrait_bounds));
        }
        
        Ok(())
    }
    
    /// Extract module-specific metadata
    fn extract_module_metadata(&amp;self, node: &amp;Node, source_code: &amp;str, metadata: &amp;mut HashMap&lt;String, Value&gt;) -&gt; Result&lt;()&gt; {
        let mut cursor = node.walk();
        let mut visibility = &quot;private&quot;.to_string();
        let mut is_inline = false;
        
        for child in node.children(&amp;mut cursor) {
            match child.kind() {
                &quot;visibility_modifier&quot; =&gt; {
                    let vis_text = child.utf8_text(source_code.as_bytes())?;
                    visibility = vis_text.to_string();
                }
                &quot;declaration_list&quot; =&gt; {
                    is_inline = true; // Has a body, so it&#x27;s an inline module
                }
                _ =&gt; {}
            }
        }
        
        metadata.insert(&quot;visibility&quot;.to_string(), Value::String(visibility));
        metadata.insert(&quot;is_inline&quot;.to_string(), Value::Bool(is_inline));
        
        Ok(())
    }
    
    /// Convert ParsedEntity to CodeEntity format
    fn convert_to_code_entity(&amp;self, entity: &amp;ParsedEntity, source_code: &amp;str) -&gt; Result&lt;CodeEntity&gt; {
        let source_lines: Vec&lt;&amp;str&gt; = source_code.lines().collect();
        let entity_source = if entity.location.start_line &lt;= source_lines.len() &amp;&amp; entity.location.end_line &lt;= source_lines.len() {
            source_lines[(entity.location.start_line - 1)..entity.location.end_line].join(&quot;\n&quot;)
        } else {
            String::new()
        };
        
        let mut code_entity = CodeEntity::new(
            entity.id.clone(),
            format!(&quot;{:?}&quot;, entity.kind),
            entity.name.clone(),
            entity.location.file_path.clone(),
        )
        .with_line_range(entity.location.start_line, entity.location.end_line)
        .with_source_code(entity_source);
        
        // Add metadata from parsed entity
        for (key, value) in &amp;entity.metadata {
            code_entity.add_property(key.clone(), value.clone());
        }
        
        Ok(code_entity)
    }
}

impl Default for RustAdapter {
    fn default() -&gt; Self {
        Self::new().expect(&quot;Failed to create Rust adapter&quot;)
    }
}

// #[cfg(test)]
// mod tests {
    use super::*;
    
    #[test]
    fn test_rust_adapter_creation() {
        let adapter = RustAdapter::new();
        assert!(adapter.is_ok());
    }
    
    #[test]
    fn test_function_parsing() {
        let mut adapter = RustAdapter::new().unwrap();
        let source_code = r#&quot;
pub fn calculate(x: i32, y: i32) -&gt; i32 {
    x + y
}

async unsafe fn complex_function() -&gt; Result&lt;(), Error&gt; {
    Ok(())
}
&quot;#;
        
        let entities = adapter.extract_code_entities(source_code, &quot;test.rs&quot;).unwrap();
        assert_eq!(entities.len(), 2);
        
        let calc_func = entities.iter().find(|e| e.name == &quot;calculate&quot;).unwrap();
        assert_eq!(calc_func.entity_type, &quot;Function&quot;);
        assert_eq!(calc_func.properties.get(&quot;visibility&quot;), Some(&amp;Value::String(&quot;pub&quot;.to_string())));
        
        let complex_func = entities.iter().find(|e| e.name == &quot;complex_function&quot;).unwrap();
        assert_eq!(complex_func.properties.get(&quot;is_async&quot;), Some(&amp;Value::Bool(true)));
        assert_eq!(complex_func.properties.get(&quot;is_unsafe&quot;), Some(&amp;Value::Bool(true)));
    }
    
    #[test]
    fn test_struct_parsing() {
        let mut adapter = RustAdapter::new().unwrap();
        let source_code = r#&quot;
pub struct User {
    id: u64,
    name: String,
    email: Option&lt;String&gt;,
}

struct Point&lt;T&gt; {
    x: T,
    y: T,
}
&quot;#;
        
        let entities = adapter.extract_code_entities(source_code, &quot;test.rs&quot;).unwrap();
        
        let struct_entities: Vec&lt;_&gt; = entities.iter().filter(|e| e.entity_type == &quot;Struct&quot;).collect();
        assert_eq!(struct_entities.len(), 2);
        
        let user_struct = struct_entities.iter().find(|e| e.name == &quot;User&quot;).unwrap();
        assert_eq!(user_struct.properties.get(&quot;visibility&quot;), Some(&amp;Value::String(&quot;pub&quot;.to_string())));
        
        let point_struct = struct_entities.iter().find(|e| e.name == &quot;Point&quot;).unwrap();
        let generic_params = point_struct.properties.get(&quot;generic_parameters&quot;);
        assert!(generic_params.is_some());
    }
    
    #[test]
    fn test_enum_parsing() {
        let mut adapter = RustAdapter::new().unwrap();
        let source_code = r#&quot;
#[derive(Debug, Clone)]
pub enum Status {
    Active,
    Inactive,
    Pending(String),
    Expired { reason: String },
}
&quot;#;
        
        let entities = adapter.extract_code_entities(source_code, &quot;test.rs&quot;).unwrap();
        assert_eq!(entities.len(), 1);
        
        let enum_entity = &amp;entities[0];
        assert_eq!(enum_entity.entity_type, &quot;Enum&quot;);
        assert_eq!(enum_entity.name, &quot;Status&quot;);
        assert_eq!(enum_entity.properties.get(&quot;visibility&quot;), Some(&amp;Value::String(&quot;pub&quot;.to_string())));
        
        let variants = enum_entity.properties.get(&quot;variants&quot;);
        assert!(variants.is_some());
    }
    
    #[test]
    fn test_trait_parsing() {
        let mut adapter = RustAdapter::new().unwrap();
        let source_code = r#&quot;
pub trait Display: Debug + Clone {
    fn fmt(&amp;self) -&gt; String;
    fn print(&amp;self) {
        println!(&quot;{}&quot;, self.fmt());
    }
}
&quot;#;
        
        let entities = adapter.extract_code_entities(source_code, &quot;test.rs&quot;).unwrap();
        assert_eq!(entities.len(), 1);
        
        let trait_entity = &amp;entities[0];
        assert_eq!(trait_entity.entity_type, &quot;Interface&quot;);
        assert_eq!(trait_entity.name, &quot;Display&quot;);
        assert_eq!(trait_entity.properties.get(&quot;visibility&quot;), Some(&amp;Value::String(&quot;pub&quot;.to_string())));
        
        let methods = trait_entity.properties.get(&quot;methods&quot;);
        assert!(methods.is_some());
    }
    
    #[test]
    fn test_module_parsing() {
        let mut adapter = RustAdapter::new().unwrap();
        let source_code = r#&quot;
pub mod utils;

mod internal {
    pub fn helper() -&gt; i32 {
        42
    }
}
&quot;#;
        
        let entities = adapter.extract_code_entities(source_code, &quot;test.rs&quot;).unwrap();
        
        let module_entities: Vec&lt;_&gt; = entities.iter().filter(|e| e.entity_type == &quot;Module&quot;).collect();
        assert!(module_entities.len() &gt;= 2); // utils and internal modules
        
        let internal_mod = module_entities.iter().find(|e| e.name == &quot;internal&quot;).unwrap();
        assert_eq!(internal_mod.properties.get(&quot;is_inline&quot;), Some(&amp;Value::Bool(true)));
    }
    
    #[test]
    fn test_const_and_static() {
        let mut adapter = RustAdapter::new().unwrap();
        let source_code = r#&quot;
const PI: f64 = 3.14159;
static GLOBAL_COUNT: AtomicUsize = AtomicUsize::new(0);
&quot;#;
        
        let entities = adapter.extract_code_entities(source_code, &quot;test.rs&quot;).unwrap();
        
        let const_entities: Vec&lt;_&gt; = entities.iter().filter(|e| e.entity_type == &quot;Constant&quot;).collect();
        assert_eq!(const_entities.len(), 2);
        
        let pi_const = const_entities.iter().find(|e| e.name == &quot;PI&quot;).unwrap();
        assert_eq!(pi_const.entity_type, &quot;Constant&quot;);
        
        let global_static = const_entities.iter().find(|e| e.name == &quot;GLOBAL_COUNT&quot;).unwrap();
        assert_eq!(global_static.entity_type, &quot;Constant&quot;);
    }

📄 vscode-extension/src/reportProvider.ts

                

                    
import * as vscode from &#x27;vscode&#x27;;
import * as fs from &#x27;fs&#x27;;
import * as path from &#x27;path&#x27;;

export class ReportProvider implements vscode.TreeDataProvider&lt;ReportItem&gt; {
    private _onDidChangeTreeData: vscode.EventEmitter&lt;ReportItem | undefined | null | void&gt; = new vscode.EventEmitter&lt;ReportItem | undefined | null | void&gt;();
    readonly onDidChangeTreeData: vscode.Event&lt;ReportItem | undefined | null | void&gt; = this._onDidChangeTreeData.event;

    constructor(private context: vscode.ExtensionContext) {}

    refresh(): void {
        this._onDidChangeTreeData.fire();
    }

    hasReports(): boolean {
        const reports = this.getReports();
        return reports.length &gt; 0;
    }

    getTreeItem(element: ReportItem): vscode.TreeItem {
        return element;
    }

    getChildren(element?: ReportItem): Thenable&lt;ReportItem[]&gt; {
        if (!element) {
            // Root level - show reports
            return Promise.resolve(this.getReports());
        } else if (element.contextValue === &#x27;report&#x27;) {
            // Report level - show file sections
            return Promise.resolve(this.getReportSections(element));
        } else if (element.contextValue === &#x27;section&#x27;) {
            // Section level - show files or issues
            return Promise.resolve(this.getSectionItems(element));
        } else {
            return Promise.resolve([]);
        }
    }

    private getReports(): ReportItem[] {
        const config = vscode.workspace.getConfiguration(&#x27;valknut&#x27;);
        const reportPath = config.get&lt;string&gt;(&#x27;reportPath&#x27;, &#x27;&#x27;);
        
        const reports: ReportItem[] = [];
        
        // Look in configured report path
        if (reportPath &amp;&amp; fs.existsSync(reportPath)) {
            this.addReportsFromDirectory(reportPath, reports);
        }
        
        // Look in workspace root
        if (vscode.workspace.workspaceFolders) {
            for (const folder of vscode.workspace.workspaceFolders) {
                const workspaceReportPath = path.join(folder.uri.fsPath, &#x27;reports&#x27;);
                if (fs.existsSync(workspaceReportPath)) {
                    this.addReportsFromDirectory(workspaceReportPath, reports);
                }
                
                // Also check for individual report files
                const files = fs.readdirSync(folder.uri.fsPath);
                for (const file of files) {
                    if (file.includes(&#x27;valknut&#x27;) &amp;&amp; file.endsWith(&#x27;.json&#x27;)) {
                        const filePath = path.join(folder.uri.fsPath, file);
                        if (this.isValidReport(filePath)) {
                            reports.push(this.createReportItem(filePath));
                        }
                    }
                }
            }
        }
        
        return reports;
    }

    private addReportsFromDirectory(dirPath: string, reports: ReportItem[]) {
        try {
            const files = fs.readdirSync(dirPath);
            for (const file of files) {
                const filePath = path.join(dirPath, file);
                const stat = fs.statSync(filePath);
                
                if (stat.isFile() &amp;&amp; file.endsWith(&#x27;.json&#x27;)) {
                    if (this.isValidReport(filePath)) {
                        reports.push(this.createReportItem(filePath));
                    }
                } else if (stat.isDirectory()) {
                    // Recursively search subdirectories
                    this.addReportsFromDirectory(filePath, reports);
                }
            }
        } catch (error) {
            console.error(&#x27;Error reading report directory:&#x27;, error);
        }
    }

    private isValidReport(filePath: string): boolean {
        try {
            const content = fs.readFileSync(filePath, &#x27;utf8&#x27;);
            const data = JSON.parse(content);
            
            // Check if it looks like a Valknut report
            return data &amp;&amp; (
                data.files || 
                data.analysis_results || 
                data.tool === &#x27;valknut&#x27; ||
                filePath.includes(&#x27;valknut&#x27;)
            );
        } catch {
            return false;
        }
    }

    private createReportItem(filePath: string): ReportItem {
        const fileName = path.basename(filePath, &#x27;.json&#x27;);
        const stats = fs.statSync(filePath);
        
        let reportData: any = {};
        try {
            const content = fs.readFileSync(filePath, &#x27;utf8&#x27;);
            reportData = JSON.parse(content);
        } catch (error) {
            console.error(&#x27;Error parsing report:&#x27;, error);
        }

        const fileCount = reportData.files?.length || 0;
        const issueCount = reportData.files?.reduce((total: number, file: any) =&gt; 
            total + (file.issues?.length || 0), 0) || 0;

        const item = new ReportItem(
            fileName,
            vscode.TreeItemCollapsibleState.Collapsed,
            {
                command: &#x27;valknut.openReport&#x27;,
                title: &#x27;Open Report&#x27;,
                arguments: [vscode.Uri.file(filePath)]
            }
        );

        item.contextValue = &#x27;report&#x27;;
        item.tooltip = `${filePath}\nFiles: ${fileCount}, Issues: ${issueCount}\nModified: ${stats.mtime.toLocaleString()}`;
        item.description = `${fileCount} files, ${issueCount} issues`;
        item.iconPath = new vscode.ThemeIcon(&#x27;file-code&#x27;);
        item.resourceUri = vscode.Uri.file(filePath);

        return item;
    }

    private getReportSections(reportItem: ReportItem): ReportItem[] {
        if (!reportItem.resourceUri) {
            return [];
        }

        try {
            const content = fs.readFileSync(reportItem.resourceUri.fsPath, &#x27;utf8&#x27;);
            const data = JSON.parse(content);
            
            const sections: ReportItem[] = [];
            
            // Files section
            if (data.files &amp;&amp; data.files.length &gt; 0) {
                const filesItem = new ReportItem(
                    `Files (${data.files.length})`,
                    vscode.TreeItemCollapsibleState.Collapsed
                );
                filesItem.contextValue = &#x27;section&#x27;;
                filesItem.iconPath = new vscode.ThemeIcon(&#x27;file-directory&#x27;);
                filesItem.sectionType = &#x27;files&#x27;;
                filesItem.reportData = data;
                sections.push(filesItem);
            }
            
            // Issues section
            const totalIssues = data.files?.reduce((total: number, file: any) =&gt; 
                total + (file.issues?.length || 0), 0) || 0;
                
            if (totalIssues &gt; 0) {
                const issuesItem = new ReportItem(
                    `Issues (${totalIssues})`,
                    vscode.TreeItemCollapsibleState.Collapsed
                );
                issuesItem.contextValue = &#x27;section&#x27;;
                issuesItem.iconPath = new vscode.ThemeIcon(&#x27;warning&#x27;);
                issuesItem.sectionType = &#x27;issues&#x27;;
                issuesItem.reportData = data;
                sections.push(issuesItem);
            }
            
            // Metrics section
            if (data.metrics || data.analysis_results) {
                const metricsItem = new ReportItem(
                    &#x27;Metrics&#x27;,
                    vscode.TreeItemCollapsibleState.Collapsed
                );
                metricsItem.contextValue = &#x27;section&#x27;;
                metricsItem.iconPath = new vscode.ThemeIcon(&#x27;graph&#x27;);
                metricsItem.sectionType = &#x27;metrics&#x27;;
                metricsItem.reportData = data;
                sections.push(metricsItem);
            }
            
            return sections;
        } catch (error) {
            console.error(&#x27;Error loading report sections:&#x27;, error);
            return [];
        }
    }

    private getSectionItems(sectionItem: ReportItem): ReportItem[] {
        if (!sectionItem.reportData) {
            return [];
        }

        const data = sectionItem.reportData;
        
        switch (sectionItem.sectionType) {
            case &#x27;files&#x27;:
                return this.getFileItems(data.files || []);
            case &#x27;issues&#x27;:
                return this.getIssueItems(data.files || []);
            case &#x27;metrics&#x27;:
                return this.getMetricItems(data);
            default:
                return [];
        }
    }

    private getFileItems(files: any[]): ReportItem[] {
        return files.map(file =&gt; {
            const issueCount = file.issues?.length || 0;
            const fileName = path.basename(file.path || &#x27;Unknown&#x27;);
            
            const item = new ReportItem(
                fileName,
                vscode.TreeItemCollapsibleState.None,
                {
                    command: &#x27;vscode.open&#x27;,
                    title: &#x27;Open File&#x27;,
                    arguments: [vscode.Uri.file(file.path)]
                }
            );
            
            item.contextValue = &#x27;file&#x27;;
            item.tooltip = `${file.path}\nSize: ${file.size || 0} bytes\nIssues: ${issueCount}`;
            item.description = issueCount &gt; 0 ? `${issueCount} issues` : &#x27;&#x27;;
            item.iconPath = issueCount &gt; 0 
                ? new vscode.ThemeIcon(&#x27;warning&#x27;, new vscode.ThemeColor(&#x27;problemsWarningIcon.foreground&#x27;))
                : new vscode.ThemeIcon(&#x27;file&#x27;);
            
            return item;
        });
    }

    private getIssueItems(files: any[]): ReportItem[] {
        const issues: ReportItem[] = [];
        
        for (const file of files) {
            if (file.issues &amp;&amp; file.issues.length &gt; 0) {
                for (const issue of file.issues) {
                    const issueLabel = `${issue.type || &#x27;Issue&#x27;}: ${issue.message || &#x27;No description&#x27;}`;
                    const fileName = path.basename(file.path || &#x27;Unknown&#x27;);
                    
                    const item = new ReportItem(
                        issueLabel,
                        vscode.TreeItemCollapsibleState.None,
                        {
                            command: &#x27;vscode.open&#x27;,
                            title: &#x27;Go to Issue&#x27;,
                            arguments: [
                                vscode.Uri.file(file.path),
                                { selection: new vscode.Range(
                                    new vscode.Position((issue.line || 1) - 1, 0),
                                    new vscode.Position((issue.line || 1) - 1, 0)
                                )}
                            ]
                        }
                    );
                    
                    item.contextValue = &#x27;issue&#x27;;
                    item.tooltip = `${fileName}:${issue.line || 1}\n${issue.message || &#x27;No description&#x27;}`;
                    item.description = `${fileName}:${issue.line || 1}`;
                    
                    // Set icon based on severity
                    const severity = issue.severity || &#x27;info&#x27;;
                    switch (severity) {
                        case &#x27;error&#x27;:
                            item.iconPath = new vscode.ThemeIcon(&#x27;error&#x27;, new vscode.ThemeColor(&#x27;problemsErrorIcon.foreground&#x27;));
                            break;
                        case &#x27;warning&#x27;:
                            item.iconPath = new vscode.ThemeIcon(&#x27;warning&#x27;, new vscode.ThemeColor(&#x27;problemsWarningIcon.foreground&#x27;));
                            break;
                        default:
                            item.iconPath = new vscode.ThemeIcon(&#x27;info&#x27;, new vscode.ThemeColor(&#x27;problemsInfoIcon.foreground&#x27;));
                    }
                    
                    issues.push(item);
                }
            }
        }
        
        return issues;
    }

    private getMetricItems(data: any): ReportItem[] {
        const metrics: ReportItem[] = [];
        
        // Add basic file metrics
        const fileCount = data.files?.length || 0;
        const totalSize = data.files?.reduce((sum: number, file: any) =&gt; sum + (file.size || 0), 0) || 0;
        const avgComplexity = fileCount &gt; 0 
            ? (data.files.reduce((sum: number, file: any) =&gt; sum + (file.complexity || 0), 0) / fileCount).toFixed(2)
            : &#x27;0.00&#x27;;
        
        metrics.push(this.createMetricItem(&#x27;Files Analyzed&#x27;, fileCount.toString()));
        metrics.push(this.createMetricItem(&#x27;Total Size&#x27;, `${(totalSize / 1024).toFixed(1)} KB`));
        metrics.push(this.createMetricItem(&#x27;Average Complexity&#x27;, avgComplexity));
        
        // Add custom metrics if available
        if (data.metrics) {
            for (const [key, value] of Object.entries(data.metrics)) {
                if (typeof value === &#x27;object&#x27;) {
                    metrics.push(this.createMetricItem(key, JSON.stringify(value)));
                } else {
                    metrics.push(this.createMetricItem(key, value?.toString() || &#x27;N/A&#x27;));
                }
            }
        }
        
        return metrics;
    }

    private createMetricItem(name: string, value: string): ReportItem {
        const item = new ReportItem(
            `${name}: ${value}`,
            vscode.TreeItemCollapsibleState.None
        );
        
        item.contextValue = &#x27;metric&#x27;;
        item.tooltip = `${name}: ${value}`;
        item.iconPath = new vscode.ThemeIcon(&#x27;symbol-numeric&#x27;);
        
        return item;
    }
}

export class ReportItem extends vscode.TreeItem {
    public sectionType?: string;
    public reportData?: any;

    constructor(
        public readonly label: string,
        public readonly collapsibleState: vscode.TreeItemCollapsibleState,
        public readonly command?: vscode.Command
    ) {
        super(label, collapsibleState);
    }
}

                

            

            

                
📄 vscode-extension/src/reportPanel.ts

                

                    
import * as vscode from &#x27;vscode&#x27;;
import * as fs from &#x27;fs&#x27;;
import * as path from &#x27;path&#x27;;

export class ReportPanel {
    public static currentPanel: ReportPanel | undefined;
    private static readonly viewType = &#x27;valknutReport&#x27;;

    private readonly _panel: vscode.WebviewPanel;
    private readonly _extensionUri: vscode.Uri;
    private _disposables: vscode.Disposable[] = [];
    private _reportData: any = null;
    private _reportPath: string;

    public static createOrShow(extensionUri: vscode.Uri, reportPath: string) {
        const column = vscode.window.activeTextEditor
            ? vscode.window.activeTextEditor.viewColumn
            : undefined;

        // If we already have a panel, show it
        if (ReportPanel.currentPanel) {
            ReportPanel.currentPanel._panel.reveal(column);
            ReportPanel.currentPanel.loadReport(reportPath);
            return;
        }

        // Otherwise, create a new panel
        const panel = vscode.window.createWebviewPanel(
            ReportPanel.viewType,
            &#x27;Valknut Report&#x27;,
            column || vscode.ViewColumn.One,
            {
                // Enable javascript in the webview
                enableScripts: true,
                // Restrict the webview to only loading content from our extension&#x27;s `media` directory
                localResourceRoots: [
                    vscode.Uri.joinPath(extensionUri, &#x27;media&#x27;),
                    vscode.Uri.joinPath(extensionUri, &#x27;..&#x27;, &#x27;themes&#x27;),
                    vscode.Uri.joinPath(extensionUri, &#x27;..&#x27;, &#x27;templates&#x27;)
                ]
            }
        );

        ReportPanel.currentPanel = new ReportPanel(panel, extensionUri, reportPath);
    }

    public static refresh() {
        if (ReportPanel.currentPanel) {
            ReportPanel.currentPanel._update();
        }
    }

    public static updateConfiguration() {
        if (ReportPanel.currentPanel) {
            ReportPanel.currentPanel._update();
        }
    }

    public static dispose() {
        if (ReportPanel.currentPanel) {
            ReportPanel.currentPanel.dispose();
        }
    }

    private constructor(panel: vscode.WebviewPanel, extensionUri: vscode.Uri, reportPath: string) {
        this._panel = panel;
        this._extensionUri = extensionUri;
        this._reportPath = reportPath;

        // Load the report data
        this.loadReport(reportPath);

        // Set the webview&#x27;s initial html content
        this._update();

        // Listen for when the panel is disposed
        this._panel.onDidDispose(() =&gt; this.dispose(), null, this._disposables);

        // Handle messages from the webview
        this._panel.webview.onDidReceiveMessage(
            message =&gt; {
                switch (message.command) {
                    case &#x27;openFile&#x27;:
                        this.openFile(message.filePath, message.line);
                        return;
                    case &#x27;exportReport&#x27;:
                        vscode.commands.executeCommand(&#x27;valknut.exportReport&#x27;);
                        return;
                    case &#x27;refreshReport&#x27;:
                        this.loadReport(this._reportPath);
                        this._update();
                        return;
                }
            },
            null,
            this._disposables
        );
    }

    private async openFile(filePath: string, line?: number) {
        try {
            // Resolve relative paths
            let fullPath = filePath;
            if (!path.isAbsolute(filePath)) {
                const workspaceRoot = vscode.workspace.workspaceFolders?.[0]?.uri.fsPath;
                if (workspaceRoot) {
                    fullPath = path.resolve(workspaceRoot, filePath);
                }
            }

            // Check if file exists
            if (!fs.existsSync(fullPath)) {
                vscode.window.showWarningMessage(`File not found: ${filePath}`);
                return;
            }

            const document = await vscode.workspace.openTextDocument(fullPath);
            const editor = await vscode.window.showTextDocument(document);

            // Jump to specific line if provided
            if (line &amp;&amp; line &gt; 0) {
                const position = new vscode.Position(line - 1, 0);
                editor.selection = new vscode.Selection(position, position);
                editor.revealRange(new vscode.Range(position, position), vscode.TextEditorRevealType.InCenter);
            }
        } catch (error) {
            vscode.window.showErrorMessage(`Failed to open file: ${error}`);
        }
    }

    private loadReport(reportPath: string) {
        try {
            if (!fs.existsSync(reportPath)) {
                vscode.window.showErrorMessage(`Report file not found: ${reportPath}`);
                return;
            }

            const reportContent = fs.readFileSync(reportPath, &#x27;utf8&#x27;);
            this._reportData = JSON.parse(reportContent);
            this._reportPath = reportPath;
            
            // Update panel title with report name
            const reportName = path.basename(reportPath, path.extname(reportPath));
            this._panel.title = `Valknut Report - ${reportName}`;
            
        } catch (error) {
            vscode.window.showErrorMessage(`Failed to load report: ${error}`);
        }
    }

    public async exportReport(outputPath: string) {
        try {
            const config = vscode.workspace.getConfiguration(&#x27;valknut&#x27;);
            const theme = config.get(&#x27;theme&#x27;, &#x27;default&#x27;);
            
            // Generate HTML report
            const html = this.generateHtmlReport(theme);
            fs.writeFileSync(outputPath, html, &#x27;utf8&#x27;);
            
        } catch (error) {
            throw new Error(`Export failed: ${error}`);
        }
    }

    private generateHtmlReport(theme: string): string {
        // This would use the Handlebars template system from the Rust code
        // For now, we&#x27;ll generate a basic HTML report
        const themeUri = vscode.Uri.joinPath(this._extensionUri, &#x27;..&#x27;, &#x27;themes&#x27;, `${theme}.css`);
        const themePath = themeUri.fsPath;
        
        let themeCSS = &#x27;&#x27;;
        try {
            if (fs.existsSync(themePath)) {
                themeCSS = fs.readFileSync(themePath, &#x27;utf8&#x27;);
            }
        } catch (error) {
            console.warn(&#x27;Failed to load theme CSS:&#x27;, error);
        }

        return `
&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;
&lt;html lang=&quot;en&quot;&gt;
&lt;head&gt;
    &lt;meta charset=&quot;UTF-8&quot;&gt;
    &lt;meta name=&quot;viewport&quot; content=&quot;width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0&quot;&gt;
    &lt;title&gt;Valknut Analysis Report&lt;/title&gt;
    &lt;style&gt;${themeCSS}&lt;/style&gt;
&lt;/head&gt;
&lt;body&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;container&quot;&gt;
        &lt;header class=&quot;header&quot;&gt;
            &lt;h1&gt;Valknut Analysis Report&lt;/h1&gt;
            &lt;div class=&quot;meta&quot;&gt;
                Generated on ${new Date().toISOString()} | Version 0.1.0
            &lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;/header&gt;
        
        &lt;section class=&quot;summary&quot;&gt;
            &lt;div class=&quot;summary-card&quot;&gt;
                &lt;div class=&quot;value&quot;&gt;${this._reportData?.files?.length || 0}&lt;/div&gt;
                &lt;div class=&quot;label&quot;&gt;Files Analyzed&lt;/div&gt;
            &lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;/section&gt;
        
        &lt;section class=&quot;results-section&quot;&gt;
            &lt;h2&gt;Analysis Results&lt;/h2&gt;
            &lt;div class=&quot;file-list&quot;&gt;
                ${this.generateFileList()}
            &lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;/section&gt;
        
        &lt;details class=&quot;raw-data&quot;&gt;
            &lt;summary&gt;Raw Data&lt;/summary&gt;
            &lt;pre&gt;&lt;code&gt;${JSON.stringify(this._reportData, null, 2)}&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;
        &lt;/details&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/body&gt;
&lt;/html&gt;`;
    }

    private generateFileList(): string {
        if (!this._reportData?.files) {
            return &#x27;&lt;p&gt;No files found in report&lt;/p&gt;&#x27;;
        }

        return this._reportData.files.map((file: any) =&gt; `
            &lt;div class=&quot;file-item&quot;&gt;
                &lt;div class=&quot;file-path&quot;&gt;${file.path || &#x27;Unknown&#x27;}&lt;/div&gt;
                &lt;div class=&quot;file-details&quot;&gt;
                    Size: ${file.size || 0} bytes
                &lt;/div&gt;
            &lt;/div&gt;
        `).join(&#x27;&#x27;);
    }

    private _update() {
        const webview = this._panel.webview;
        this._panel.webview.html = this._getHtmlForWebview(webview);
    }

    private _getHtmlForWebview(webview: vscode.Webview): string {
        if (!this._reportData) {
            return this._getLoadingHtml();
        }

        const config = vscode.workspace.getConfiguration(&#x27;valknut&#x27;);
        const theme = config.get(&#x27;theme&#x27;, &#x27;default&#x27;);
        
        // Get theme CSS
        const themeUri = vscode.Uri.joinPath(this._extensionUri, &#x27;..&#x27;, &#x27;themes&#x27;, `${theme}.css`);
        const themeCSS = webview.asWebviewUri(themeUri);

        return `&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;
&lt;html lang=&quot;en&quot;&gt;
&lt;head&gt;
    &lt;meta charset=&quot;UTF-8&quot;&gt;
    &lt;meta name=&quot;viewport&quot; content=&quot;width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0&quot;&gt;
    &lt;title&gt;Valknut Report&lt;/title&gt;
    &lt;link href=&quot;${themeCSS}&quot; rel=&quot;stylesheet&quot;&gt;
    &lt;style&gt;
        /* VS Code integration styles */
        .toolbar {
            position: fixed;
            top: 10px;
            right: 10px;
            display: flex;
            gap: 8px;
            z-index: 1000;
        }
        
        .toolbar button {
            background: var(--primary-color);
            color: white;
            border: none;
            padding: 8px 12px;
            border-radius: 4px;
            cursor: pointer;
            font-size: 12px;
            transition: opacity 0.2s;
        }
        
        .toolbar button:hover {
            opacity: 0.8;
        }
        
        .status-bar {
            position: fixed;
            bottom: 0;
            left: 0;
            right: 0;
            background: var(--surface-color);
            border-top: 1px solid var(--border-color);
            padding: 8px 16px;
            font-size: 12px;
            color: var(--text-secondary);
        }
    &lt;/style&gt;
&lt;/head&gt;
&lt;body&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;toolbar&quot;&gt;
        &lt;button onclick=&quot;refreshReport()&quot;&gt;Refresh&lt;/button&gt;
        &lt;button onclick=&quot;exportReport()&quot;&gt;Export&lt;/button&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
    
    &lt;div class=&quot;container&quot;&gt;
        &lt;header class=&quot;header&quot;&gt;
            &lt;h1&gt;Valknut Analysis Report&lt;/h1&gt;
            &lt;div class=&quot;meta&quot;&gt;
                Report: ${path.basename(this._reportPath)} | Generated on ${new Date().toISOString()}
            &lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;/header&gt;
        
        &lt;section class=&quot;summary&quot;&gt;
            ${this.generateSummaryCards()}
        &lt;/section&gt;
        
        &lt;section class=&quot;results-section&quot;&gt;
            &lt;h2&gt;File Analysis&lt;/h2&gt;
            &lt;div class=&quot;file-list&quot;&gt;
                ${this.generateInteractiveFileList()}
            &lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;/section&gt;
        
        ${this.generateIssuesSection()}
        
        &lt;details class=&quot;raw-data&quot;&gt;
            &lt;summary&gt;Raw Data&lt;/summary&gt;
            &lt;pre&gt;&lt;code&gt;${JSON.stringify(this._reportData, null, 2)}&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;
        &lt;/details&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
    
    &lt;div class=&quot;status-bar&quot;&gt;
        &lt;span&gt;Report loaded: ${this._reportPath}&lt;/span&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
    
    &lt;script&gt;
        const vscode = acquireVsCodeApi();
        
        function refreshReport() {
            vscode.postMessage({ command: &#x27;refreshReport&#x27; });
        }
        
        function exportReport() {
            vscode.postMessage({ command: &#x27;exportReport&#x27; });
        }
        
        function openFile(filePath, line) {
            vscode.postMessage({ 
                command: &#x27;openFile&#x27;,
                filePath: filePath,
                line: line
            });
        }
        
        // Add click handlers for file items
        document.addEventListener(&#x27;DOMContentLoaded&#x27;, function() {
            const fileItems = document.querySelectorAll(&#x27;.file-item[data-file-path]&#x27;);
            fileItems.forEach(item =&gt; {
                item.addEventListener(&#x27;click&#x27;, function() {
                    const filePath = this.dataset.filePath;
                    const line = parseInt(this.dataset.line || &#x27;1&#x27;);
                    openFile(filePath, line);
                });
            });
            
            // Add click handlers for issue items
            const issueItems = document.querySelectorAll(&#x27;.issue-item[data-line]&#x27;);
            issueItems.forEach(item =&gt; {
                item.addEventListener(&#x27;click&#x27;, function(e) {
                    e.stopPropagation();
                    const filePath = this.closest(&#x27;.file-item&#x27;).dataset.filePath;
                    const line = parseInt(this.dataset.line || &#x27;1&#x27;);
                    openFile(filePath, line);
                });
            });
        });
    &lt;/script&gt;
&lt;/body&gt;
&lt;/html&gt;`;
    }

    private generateSummaryCards(): string {
        const files = this._reportData?.files || [];
        const totalFiles = files.length;
        const totalIssues = files.reduce((total: number, file: any) =&gt; {
            return total + (file.issues?.length || 0);
        }, 0);
        const avgComplexity = files.length &gt; 0 
            ? (files.reduce((sum: number, file: any) =&gt; sum + (file.complexity || 0), 0) / files.length).toFixed(1)
            : &#x27;0.0&#x27;;

        return `
            &lt;div class=&quot;summary-card&quot;&gt;
                &lt;div class=&quot;value&quot;&gt;${totalFiles}&lt;/div&gt;
                &lt;div class=&quot;label&quot;&gt;Files Analyzed&lt;/div&gt;
            &lt;/div&gt;
            &lt;div class=&quot;summary-card&quot;&gt;
                &lt;div class=&quot;value&quot;&gt;${totalIssues}&lt;/div&gt;
                &lt;div class=&quot;label&quot;&gt;Issues Found&lt;/div&gt;
            &lt;/div&gt;
            &lt;div class=&quot;summary-card&quot;&gt;
                &lt;div class=&quot;value&quot;&gt;${avgComplexity}&lt;/div&gt;
                &lt;div class=&quot;label&quot;&gt;Avg Complexity&lt;/div&gt;
            &lt;/div&gt;
        `;
    }

    private generateInteractiveFileList(): string {
        const files = this._reportData?.files || [];
        
        return files.map((file: any) =&gt; {
            const issuesCount = file.issues?.length || 0;
            const badgeClass = issuesCount &gt; 0 ? &#x27;error&#x27; : &#x27;success&#x27;;
            const badgeText = issuesCount &gt; 0 ? `${issuesCount} issues` : &#x27;Clean&#x27;;
            
            return `
                &lt;div class=&quot;file-item&quot; data-file-path=&quot;${file.path}&quot; data-line=&quot;1&quot;&gt;
                    &lt;div class=&quot;file-header&quot;&gt;
                        &lt;div class=&quot;file-path&quot;&gt;${file.path}&lt;/div&gt;
                        &lt;div class=&quot;file-badge&quot;&gt;
                            &lt;span class=&quot;badge ${badgeClass}&quot;&gt;${badgeText}&lt;/span&gt;
                        &lt;/div&gt;
                    &lt;/div&gt;
                    &lt;div class=&quot;file-details&quot;&gt;
                        &lt;span&gt;Size: ${file.size || 0} bytes&lt;/span&gt;
                        ${file.complexity ? `&lt;span&gt;Complexity: ${file.complexity}&lt;/span&gt;` : &#x27;&#x27;}
                        ${file.language ? `&lt;span&gt;Language: ${file.language}&lt;/span&gt;` : &#x27;&#x27;}
                    &lt;/div&gt;
                    ${this.generateIssuesPreview(file.issues)}
                &lt;/div&gt;
            `;
        }).join(&#x27;&#x27;);
    }

    private generateIssuesPreview(issues: any[]): string {
        if (!issues || issues.length === 0) {
            return &#x27;&#x27;;
        }

        return `
            &lt;div class=&quot;issues-preview&quot;&gt;
                ${issues.map(issue =&gt; `
                    &lt;div class=&quot;issue-item&quot; data-line=&quot;${issue.line || 1}&quot;&gt;
                        &lt;span class=&quot;issue-type ${issue.severity || &#x27;info&#x27;}&quot;&gt;${issue.type || &#x27;Issue&#x27;}&lt;/span&gt;
                        &lt;span class=&quot;issue-message&quot;&gt;${issue.message || &#x27;No description&#x27;}&lt;/span&gt;
                        ${issue.line ? `&lt;span class=&quot;issue-location&quot;&gt;Line ${issue.line}&lt;/span&gt;` : &#x27;&#x27;}
                    &lt;/div&gt;
                `).join(&#x27;&#x27;)}
            &lt;/div&gt;
        `;
    }

    private generateIssuesSection(): string {
        const files = this._reportData?.files || [];
        const allIssues = files.flatMap((file: any) =&gt; 
            (file.issues || []).map((issue: any) =&gt; ({ ...issue, file: file.path }))
        );

        if (allIssues.length === 0) {
            return &#x27;&#x27;;
        }

        return `
            &lt;section class=&quot;results-section&quot;&gt;
                &lt;h2&gt;All Issues (${allIssues.length})&lt;/h2&gt;
                &lt;div class=&quot;issues-list&quot;&gt;
                    ${allIssues.map(issue =&gt; `
                        &lt;div class=&quot;issue-item-full&quot; data-file-path=&quot;${issue.file}&quot; data-line=&quot;${issue.line || 1}&quot;&gt;
                            &lt;div class=&quot;issue-header&quot;&gt;
                                &lt;span class=&quot;issue-type ${issue.severity || &#x27;info&#x27;}&quot;&gt;${issue.type || &#x27;Issue&#x27;}&lt;/span&gt;
                                &lt;span class=&quot;issue-file&quot;&gt;${issue.file}${issue.line ? `:${issue.line}` : &#x27;&#x27;}&lt;/span&gt;
                            &lt;/div&gt;
                            &lt;div class=&quot;issue-message&quot;&gt;${issue.message || &#x27;No description&#x27;}&lt;/div&gt;
                        &lt;/div&gt;
                    `).join(&#x27;&#x27;)}
                &lt;/div&gt;
            &lt;/section&gt;
        `;
    }

    private _getLoadingHtml(): string {
        return `&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;
&lt;html lang=&quot;en&quot;&gt;
&lt;head&gt;
    &lt;meta charset=&quot;UTF-8&quot;&gt;
    &lt;meta name=&quot;viewport&quot; content=&quot;width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0&quot;&gt;
    &lt;title&gt;Loading Report&lt;/title&gt;
    &lt;style&gt;
        body {
            font-family: system-ui, sans-serif;
            display: flex;
            justify-content: center;
            align-items: center;
            height: 100vh;
            margin: 0;
            background: var(--vscode-editor-background);
            color: var(--vscode-editor-foreground);
        }
        .loading {
            text-align: center;
        }
        .spinner {
            border: 3px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.3);
            border-radius: 50%;
            border-top: 3px solid var(--vscode-progressBar-background);
            width: 40px;
            height: 40px;
            animation: spin 1s linear infinite;
            margin: 0 auto 1rem;
        }
        @keyframes spin {
            0% { transform: rotate(0deg); }
            100% { transform: rotate(360deg); }
        }
    &lt;/style&gt;
&lt;/head&gt;
&lt;body&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;loading&quot;&gt;
        &lt;div class=&quot;spinner&quot;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;p&gt;Loading Valknut report...&lt;/p&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/body&gt;
&lt;/html&gt;`;
    }

    public dispose() {
        ReportPanel.currentPanel = undefined;

        // Clean up our resources
        this._panel.dispose();

        while (this._disposables.length) {
            const x = this._disposables.pop();
            if (x) {
                x.dispose();
            }
        }
    }
}
