📄 ci-examples/jenkins.groovy

                

                    
// Jenkins Pipeline - Code Quality Gate with Valknut
pipeline {
    agent any
    
    environment {
        VALKNUT_VERSION = &#x27;latest&#x27;
    }
    
    stages {
        stage(&#x27;Checkout&#x27;) {
            steps {
                checkout scm
            }
        }
        
        stage(&#x27;Setup Valknut&#x27;) {
            steps {
                script {
                    // Download Valknut binary
                    sh &#x27;&#x27;&#x27;
                        curl -L -o valknut &quot;https://github.com/your-repo/valknut/releases/latest/download/valknut-linux-x86_64&quot;
                        chmod +x valknut
                    &#x27;&#x27;&#x27;
                }
            }
        }
        
        stage(&#x27;Code Quality Analysis&#x27;) {
            steps {
                script {
                    // Run analysis with quality gates
                    def analysisResult = sh(
                        script: &#x27;&#x27;&#x27;
                            ./valknut analyze . \
                              --format ci-summary \
                              --quality-gate \
                              --max-issues 5 \
                              --min-health 70 \
                              --max-complexity 80 \
                              --min-maintainability 60 \
                              --quiet
                        &#x27;&#x27;&#x27;,
                        returnStatus: true
                    )
                    
                    // Parse results
                    if (fileExists(&#x27;out/ci_summary.json&#x27;)) {
                        def results = readJSON file: &#x27;out/ci_summary.json&#x27;
                        
                        echo &quot;Quality Analysis Results:&quot;
                        echo &quot;========================&quot;
                        echo &quot;Status: ${results.status}&quot;
                        echo &quot;Health Score: ${results.metrics.overall_health_score}&quot;
                        echo &quot;Total Issues: ${results.summary.total_issues}&quot;
                        echo &quot;Critical Issues: ${results.summary.critical_issues}&quot;
                        
                        // Set build properties
                        currentBuild.displayName = &quot;#${env.BUILD_NUMBER} - Health: ${results.metrics.overall_health_score}%&quot;
                        
                        if (results.summary.total_issues &gt; 0) {
                            echo &quot;Recommendations:&quot;
                            results.quality_gates.recommendations.each { rec -&gt;
                                echo &quot;- ${rec}&quot;
                            }
                        }
                        
                        // Create quality gate summary
                        def summary = [
                            healthScore: results.metrics.overall_health_score,
                            totalIssues: results.summary.total_issues,
                            criticalIssues: results.summary.critical_issues,
                            status: results.status
                        ]
                        
                        writeJSON file: &#x27;quality_summary.json&#x27;, json: summary
                        
                        // Fail the build if quality gates failed
                        if (analysisResult != 0) {
                            currentBuild.result = &#x27;UNSTABLE&#x27;
                            error(&quot;Quality gates failed! Health Score: ${results.metrics.overall_health_score}%, Issues: ${results.summary.total_issues}&quot;)
                        }
                    } else {
                        error(&quot;Analysis results not found&quot;)
                    }
                }
            }
            post {
                always {
                    // Archive analysis results
                    archiveArtifacts artifacts: &#x27;out/**/*&#x27;, allowEmptyArchive: true
                    archiveArtifacts artifacts: &#x27;quality_summary.json&#x27;, allowEmptyArchive: true
                }
            }
        }
        
        stage(&#x27;Generate Reports&#x27;) {
            when {
                anyOf {
                    branch &#x27;main&#x27;
                    branch &#x27;develop&#x27;
                }
            }
            steps {
                script {
                    // Generate detailed HTML report for main branches
                    sh &#x27;&#x27;&#x27;
                        ./valknut analyze . \
                          --format html \
                          --out detailed-report \
                          --quiet
                    &#x27;&#x27;&#x27;
                    
                    // Publish HTML report
                    publishHTML([
                        allowMissing: false,
                        alwaysLinkToLastBuild: true,
                        keepAll: true,
                        reportDir: &#x27;detailed-report&#x27;,
                        reportFiles: &#x27;team_report.html&#x27;,
                        reportName: &#x27;Valknut Code Quality Report&#x27;
                    ])
                }
            }
        }
    }
    
    post {
        always {
            // Clean workspace
            cleanWs()
        }
        
        success {
            echo &quot;✅ Pipeline completed successfully!&quot;
            
            // Send notification for successful quality gates
            script {
                if (fileExists(&#x27;quality_summary.json&#x27;)) {
                    def summary = readJSON file: &#x27;quality_summary.json&#x27;
                    if (summary.status == &#x27;success&#x27;) {
                        // You can add Slack/Teams notification here
                        echo &quot;Quality gates passed! Health Score: ${summary.healthScore}%&quot;
                    }
                }
            }
        }
        
        unstable {
            echo &quot;⚠️ Pipeline completed with quality issues&quot;
            
            // Send notification for failed quality gates
            script {
                if (fileExists(&#x27;quality_summary.json&#x27;)) {
                    def summary = readJSON file: &#x27;quality_summary.json&#x27;
                    // You can add Slack/Teams notification here
                    echo &quot;Quality gates failed! Health Score: ${summary.healthScore}%, Issues: ${summary.totalIssues}&quot;
                }
            }
        }
        
        failure {
            echo &quot;❌ Pipeline failed&quot;
        }
    }
}

                

            

            

                
📄 scripts/release.sh

                

                    
#!/bin/bash
# Release script for Valknut

set -e

VERSION=${1:-}

if [ -z &quot;$VERSION&quot; ]; then
    echo &quot;Usage: ./scripts/release.sh &lt;version&gt;&quot;
    echo &quot;Example: ./scripts/release.sh 0.1.0&quot;
    exit 1
fi

echo &quot;Creating release for Valknut v$VERSION&quot;

# Update version in Cargo.toml
sed -i.bak &quot;s/^version = .*/version = \&quot;$VERSION\&quot;/&quot; Cargo.toml
rm Cargo.toml.bak

# Build release binary
echo &quot;Building release binary...&quot;
cargo build --release

# Create git tag
echo &quot;Creating git tag v$VERSION...&quot;
git add Cargo.toml Cargo.lock
git commit -m &quot;Release v$VERSION&quot; || true
git tag -a &quot;v$VERSION&quot; -m &quot;Release v$VERSION&quot;

echo &quot;Release v$VERSION created!&quot;
echo &quot;&quot;
echo &quot;Next steps:&quot;
echo &quot;1. Push the tag: git push origin v$VERSION&quot;
echo &quot;2. Create a GitHub release with the tag&quot;
echo &quot;3. Upload the binary from target/release/valknut&quot;
echo &quot;4. Update the Homebrew formula with the release URL and SHA256&quot;

📄 scripts/install_parsers.sh

                

                    
#!/bin/bash
# Tree-sitter Parser Installation Script for Valknut
# This script installs all required tree-sitter language parsers

set -euo pipefail

echo &quot;🌳 Installing Tree-sitter Language Parsers for Valknut&quot;
echo &quot;=================================================&quot;

# Check if we&#x27;re in a virtual environment
if [[ &quot;${VIRTUAL_ENV:-}&quot; == &quot;&quot; ]]; then
    echo &quot;⚠️  Warning: Not in a virtual environment. Consider activating one first.&quot;
    echo &quot;   Example: python3 -m venv venv &amp;&amp; source venv/bin/activate&quot;
    echo &quot;&quot;
fi

echo &quot;📦 Installing core tree-sitter parsers...&quot;

# Core language parsers for the enhanced valknut
parsers=(
    &quot;tree-sitter-python&gt;=0.20.0&quot;
    &quot;tree-sitter-javascript&gt;=0.20.0&quot; 
    &quot;tree-sitter-typescript&gt;=0.20.0&quot;
    &quot;tree-sitter-rust&gt;=0.20.0&quot;
    &quot;tree-sitter-go&gt;=0.20.0&quot;
    &quot;tree-sitter-bash&gt;=0.20.0&quot;
)

for parser in &quot;${parsers[@]}&quot;; do
    echo &quot;  Installing $parser...&quot;
    if pip install &quot;$parser&quot;; then
        echo &quot;  ✅ $parser installed successfully&quot;
    else
        echo &quot;  ❌ Failed to install $parser&quot;
        echo &quot;  📝 Note: This parser may not be available. Valknut will gracefully handle missing parsers.&quot;
    fi
done

echo &quot;&quot;
echo &quot;🔍 Verifying installation...&quot;

# Test imports
python3 -c &quot;
import sys

parsers = [
    (&#x27;tree_sitter_python&#x27;, &#x27;Python&#x27;),
    (&#x27;tree_sitter_javascript&#x27;, &#x27;JavaScript&#x27;),
    (&#x27;tree_sitter_typescript&#x27;, &#x27;TypeScript&#x27;),
    (&#x27;tree_sitter_rust&#x27;, &#x27;Rust&#x27;),
    (&#x27;tree_sitter_go&#x27;, &#x27;Go&#x27;),
    (&#x27;tree_sitter_bash&#x27;, &#x27;Bash&#x27;)
]

available = []
unavailable = []

for module, name in parsers:
    try:
        __import__(module)
        available.append(name)
        print(f&#x27;✅ {name} parser available&#x27;)
    except ImportError:
        unavailable.append(name)
        print(f&#x27;❌ {name} parser not available&#x27;)

print()
print(f&#x27;📊 Summary: {len(available)}/{len(parsers)} parsers available&#x27;)
print(f&#x27;✅ Available: {&#x27;, &#x27;.join(available)}&#x27;)
if unavailable:
    print(f&#x27;❌ Unavailable: {&#x27;, &#x27;.join(unavailable)}&#x27;)
print()
print(&#x27;🎯 Valknut will use available parsers and gracefully handle missing ones.&#x27;)
&quot;

echo &quot;&quot;
echo &quot;🎉 Parser installation complete!&quot;
echo &quot;🚀 You can now run: python3 -m valknut --help&quot;
echo &quot;&quot;
echo &quot;💡 If any parsers failed to install, Valknut will still work with available parsers.&quot;
echo &quot;   Check individual parser documentation for installation troubleshooting.&quot;

        // Filter dropdown functionality
        function toggleFilterMenu() {
            const menu = document.getElementById(&#x27;filter-menu&#x27;);
            const button = document.getElementById(&#x27;filter-button&#x27;);
            const chevron = button.querySelector(&#x27;[data-lucide=&quot;chevron-down&quot;]&#x27;);
            
            if (menu.style.display === &#x27;none&#x27;) {
                menu.style.display = &#x27;block&#x27;;
                chevron.style.transform = &#x27;rotate(180deg)&#x27;;
            } else {
                menu.style.display = &#x27;none&#x27;;
                chevron.style.transform = &#x27;rotate(0deg)&#x27;;
            }
        }
        
        // Close filter menu when clicking outside
        document.addEventListener(&#x27;click&#x27;, function(event) {
            const dropdown = document.querySelector(&#x27;.filter-dropdown&#x27;);
            const menu = document.getElementById(&#x27;filter-menu&#x27;);
            
            if (!dropdown.contains(event.target)) {
                menu.style.display = &#x27;none&#x27;;
                const chevron = document.querySelector(&#x27;#filter-button [data-lucide=&quot;chevron-down&quot;]&#x27;);
                chevron.style.transform = &#x27;rotate(0deg)&#x27;;
            }
        });
        
        // Apply filters based on checkboxes
        function applyFilters() {
            const highComplexityOnly = document.getElementById(&#x27;filter-high-complexity&#x27;).checked;
            const extractMethod = document.getElementById(&#x27;filter-extract-method&#x27;).checked;
            const simplifyConditionals = document.getElementById(&#x27;filter-simplify-conditionals&#x27;).checked;
            const improveStructure = document.getElementById(&#x27;filter-improve-structure&#x27;).checked;
            const generalRefactoring = document.getElementById(&#x27;filter-general-refactoring&#x27;).checked;
            
            const fileNodes = document.querySelectorAll(&#x27;.file-node&#x27;);
            
            fileNodes.forEach(fileNode =&gt; {
                let shouldShow = false;
                
                // Check if file meets complexity filter
                const priority = fileNode.getAttribute(&#x27;data-priority&#x27;);
                const meetsComplexityFilter = !highComplexityOnly || priority === &#x27;Critical&#x27; || priority === &#x27;High&#x27;;
                
                if (meetsComplexityFilter) {
                    // Check if file has any refactoring suggestions that match the selected types
                    const suggestions = fileNode.querySelectorAll(&#x27;.suggestion-item&#x27;);
                    if (suggestions.length === 0) {
                        // If no specific suggestions found, show the file (it might have general refactoring needs)
                        shouldShow = true;
                    } else {
                        // Check each suggestion to see if it matches selected refactoring types
                        suggestions.forEach(suggestion =&gt; {
                            const suggestionText = suggestion.textContent.toLowerCase();
                            if ((extractMethod &amp;&amp; suggestionText.includes(&#x27;extract&#x27;)) ||
                                (simplifyConditionals &amp;&amp; suggestionText.includes(&#x27;conditional&#x27;)) ||
                                (improveStructure &amp;&amp; suggestionText.includes(&#x27;structure&#x27;)) ||
                                (generalRefactoring &amp;&amp; !suggestionText.includes(&#x27;extract&#x27;) &amp;&amp; 
                                 !suggestionText.includes(&#x27;conditional&#x27;) &amp;&amp; !suggestionText.includes(&#x27;structure&#x27;))) {
                                shouldShow = true;
                            }
                        });
                    }
                }
                
                // Apply filter
                if (shouldShow) {
                    fileNode.classList.remove(&#x27;filtered-out&#x27;);
                } else {
                    fileNode.classList.add(&#x27;filtered-out&#x27;);
                }
            });
            
            // Log filtering results
            const visibleFiles = document.querySelectorAll(&#x27;.file-node:not(.filtered-out)&#x27;).length;
            const totalFiles = fileNodes.length;
            console.log(`Filter: Showing ${visibleFiles} of ${totalFiles} files`);
        }
        
        // Enhanced tree functionality inspired by Arbiter FileTree
        function toggleTreeNode(headerElement) {
            const treeNode = headerElement.closest(&#x27;.tree-node&#x27;);
            const chevron = headerElement.querySelector(&#x27;.tree-chevron&#x27;);
            const children = treeNode.querySelector(&#x27;.tree-children&#x27;);
            
            if (!children) return;
            
            const isExpanded = headerElement.getAttribute(&#x27;aria-expanded&#x27;) === &#x27;true&#x27;;
            
            // Toggle expanded state
            headerElement.setAttribute(&#x27;aria-expanded&#x27;, !isExpanded);
            treeNode.classList.toggle(&#x27;tree-expanded&#x27;, !isExpanded);
            
            // Toggle children visibility with smooth animation
            if (isExpanded) {
                children.classList.add(&#x27;collapsed&#x27;);
                children.classList.remove(&#x27;expanded&#x27;);
            } else {
                children.classList.remove(&#x27;collapsed&#x27;);
                children.classList.add(&#x27;expanded&#x27;);
            }
            
            // Rotate chevron
            if (chevron) {
                chevron.style.transform = isExpanded ? &#x27;rotate(0deg)&#x27; : &#x27;rotate(90deg)&#x27;;
            }
        }
        
        // Keyboard navigation
        document.addEventListener(&#x27;keydown&#x27;, function(e) {
            if (e.target.classList.contains(&#x27;tree-expandable&#x27;)) {
                if (e.key === &#x27;Enter&#x27; || e.key === &#x27; &#x27;) {
                    e.preventDefault();
                    toggleTreeNode(e.target);
                }
            }
        });
        
        // Auto-expand critical and high priority items
        document.addEventListener(&#x27;DOMContentLoaded&#x27;, function() {
            // Auto-expand functionality removed to keep all nodes collapsed by default
            // Users can manually expand file nodes as needed
            
            // Initialize all chevrons to point right (collapsed state)
            document.querySelectorAll(&#x27;.tree-chevron&#x27;).forEach(chevron =&gt; {
                chevron.style.transform = &#x27;rotate(0deg)&#x27;;
            });
            
            {{#if enable_animation}}
            // Initialize trefoil animation if enabled
            if (typeof window.initTrefoilAnimation === &#x27;function&#x27;) {
                const canvas = document.getElementById(&#x27;neural-network&#x27;);
                if (canvas) {
                    window.initTrefoilAnimation(canvas);
                }
            }
            {{/if}}
            
            console.log(`Target: Valknut Analysis Report Loaded`);
            console.log(`Chart: Found ${document.querySelectorAll(&#x27;.tree-node&#x27;).length} refactoring candidates`);
            console.log(`Palette: Using Sibylline Design System Theme`);
            
            // Initialize Lucide icons
            lucide.createIcons();
        });
        
        // Smooth scrolling for tree navigation
        function scrollToNode(nodeId) {
            const element = document.getElementById(nodeId);
            if (element) {
                element.scrollIntoView({ 
                    behavior: &#x27;smooth&#x27;, 
                    block: &#x27;center&#x27; 
                });
            }
        }
        
        // Initialize Lucide icons when DOM is loaded
        document.addEventListener(&#x27;DOMContentLoaded&#x27;, function() {
            lucide.createIcons();
        });

        // Oracle phase toggle functionality
        function togglePhase(element) {
            const phaseCard = element.closest(&#x27;.phase-card&#x27;);
            const phaseContent = phaseCard.querySelector(&#x27;.phase-content&#x27;);
            const chevron = element.querySelector(&#x27;[data-lucide=&quot;chevron-right&quot;]&#x27;);
            
            if (phaseContent.style.display === &#x27;none&#x27;) {
                phaseContent.style.display = &#x27;block&#x27;;
                chevron.style.transform = &#x27;rotate(90deg)&#x27;;
            } else {
                phaseContent.style.display = &#x27;none&#x27;;
                chevron.style.transform = &#x27;rotate(0deg)&#x27;;
            }
        }

        // Helper function to capitalize strings (for Handlebars templates that might need it)
        function capitalize(str) {
            if (!str) return &#x27;&#x27;;
            return str.charAt(0).toUpperCase() + str.slice(1).toLowerCase();
        }
    &lt;/script&gt;
&lt;/body&gt;

/* Valknut Report Theme - Sibylline Design System Integration */
/* Professional minimalist design system adapted from webpage.html */

  /* Font families - matching webpage.html */
  --font-family-default: &#x27;Inter&#x27;, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &#x27;Segoe UI&#x27;, system-ui, sans-serif;
  --font-family-display: &#x27;Inter&#x27;, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &#x27;Segoe UI&#x27;, system-ui, sans-serif;
  --font-family-monospace: &#x27;SF Mono&#x27;, &#x27;Monaco&#x27;, &#x27;Consolas&#x27;, &#x27;Liberation Mono&#x27;, monospace;
  
  /* Sophisticated graphite palette - from webpage.html */
